WEBVTT

00:03.937 --> 00:07.007
[MEN'S CHORUS]
* OHH-OHH *

00:07.007 --> 00:12.413
* OHH-OHH-OHH *

00:12.413 --> 00:19.753
* AHH-AHH-AHH-AHH *

00:19.753 --> 00:26.760
* AH-AH-AH-AH-AH *

00:26.760 --> 00:32.031
* OHH... **

00:32.031 --> 00:33.734
IT'S 7 A.M., CHILDREN,

00:33.734 --> 00:36.304
AND YOU'RE LISTENING
TO RADIO FREE HARVARD

00:36.304 --> 00:38.306
ON A CHILLY
NOVEMBER MORNING.

00:38.306 --> 00:41.175
YOU'RE AT THE GREATEST
UNIVERSITY ON EARTH,

00:41.175 --> 00:42.476
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:42.476 --> 00:44.312
YOU'RE IN
OVER YOUR HEAD.

00:44.312 --> 00:45.313
YOU'RE DROWNING,

00:45.313 --> 00:46.714
ESPECIALLY YOU SENIORS.

00:46.714 --> 00:49.317
ONLY 150 DAYS BEFORE
YOUR THESIS IS DUE

00:49.317 --> 00:51.185
AND THE POWERS THAT BE

00:51.185 --> 00:53.187
DECIDE WHETHER YOU'RE
DESTINED FOR GREATNESS

00:53.187 --> 00:55.489
OR MEDIOCRITY.

00:55.489 --> 00:57.491
I KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING.

00:57.491 --> 00:59.693
DO I REALLY BELONG HERE?

00:59.693 --> 01:00.694
PROBABLY NOT.

01:00.694 --> 01:03.597
BUT DON'T GIVE IN.
DON'T GIVE UP.

01:03.597 --> 01:05.599
ARISE, FAIR HARVARD.
ARISE.

01:05.599 --> 01:08.602
YOU, TOO,
CAN RULE THE WORLD.

01:08.602 --> 01:12.206
YOU JUST HAVE TO CRUSH
EVERYONE ELSE FIRST.

01:12.206 --> 01:14.775
A LITTLE CRUSHING
MUSIC, MAESTRO.

01:14.775 --> 01:16.577
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS]

01:16.577 --> 01:19.780
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
WARNER BROS.

01:48.976 --> 01:52.246
ALL RIGHT, GUYS,
LET'S GO!

01:58.986 --> 02:01.422
KEEP GOING! KEEP GOING.

02:09.363 --> 02:12.566
KEEP UP THE PACE!
NICE AND NEAT!

02:12.566 --> 02:13.734
WHOO!

02:15.135 --> 02:17.037
IGNORE HIM!

02:17.037 --> 02:19.307
MOVE IT. LET'S GO!

02:20.274 --> 02:21.609
WHOO-HOO!

02:23.010 --> 02:25.746
VERY FUNNY, MONTY.

02:32.253 --> 02:34.288
NOW HERE'S SOMETHING
TO CROW ABOUT.

02:34.288 --> 02:35.323
[ROOSTER CROWS]

02:35.323 --> 02:37.691
I'VE GOT A GREAT COCK,
DON'T I?

02:37.691 --> 02:39.293
LAST NIGHT
A RADCLIFFE SOPHOMORE

02:39.293 --> 02:41.895
SAW A GHOST LOOKING
REMARKABLY LIKE WALT WHITMAN

02:41.895 --> 02:43.297
IN WIDENER LIBRARY.

02:43.297 --> 02:46.099
AMERICA'S GREATEST POET
HAUNTING THE STACKS, EH?

02:46.099 --> 02:48.702
WELL, THE CLIFFIE IS UNDERGOING
SOME INTENSE DEBRIEFING

02:48.702 --> 02:51.705
BY THE ENGLISH DEPARTMENT.
THEY BETTER HURRY.

02:51.705 --> 02:55.309
WEATHER TELLS US
THAT 10 INCHES
OF THE WHITE SHROUD

02:55.309 --> 02:56.710
IS SCHEDULED FOR TONIGHT.

02:56.710 --> 02:59.313
I'M EVERETT CALLOWAY.
NOW YOU HEAR ME...

02:59.313 --> 03:00.748
NOW YOU...

03:00.748 --> 03:04.318
YOUR FATHER CALLED
AND WANTS YOU
TO CALL HIM BACK.

03:04.318 --> 03:05.919
WHAT'S UP
WITH FATHER?

03:05.919 --> 03:07.321
MARRYING MY SISTER,
PERHAPS?

03:07.321 --> 03:11.492
HE MUMBLED SOMETHING
ABOUT YOUR BEING
OVERDRAWN...

03:11.492 --> 03:12.626
AGAIN.

03:13.927 --> 03:16.330
I THOUGHT
HE WAS A PATRIOT.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.766
DOESN'T HE BELIEVE
IN DEFICIT SPENDING?

03:18.766 --> 03:20.701
LORD MONTAGUE,

03:20.701 --> 03:24.305
YOU'RE LOOKING VERY GRIM
AND FORMAL THIS MORNING.

03:24.305 --> 03:26.206
TRYING TO PASS
FOR A YALIE?

03:26.206 --> 03:28.208
I GOT A MEETING
WITH PITKANNAN.

03:28.208 --> 03:31.945
OH, NO. NOT
ABOUT THE THESIS.

03:31.945 --> 03:32.946
FEELING CONFIDENT?

03:32.946 --> 03:34.047
FEELING NAUSEOUS.

03:34.047 --> 03:36.750
LOOK AT THIS ONE HERE.
LOOK AT HER.

03:36.750 --> 03:37.751
OH, GOD.

03:37.751 --> 03:38.952
HI.

03:38.952 --> 03:40.354
I KNOW HER.

03:40.354 --> 03:41.955
I'VE BEEN WITH HER.

03:41.955 --> 03:44.325
FIRST PARAGRAPH,
MR. KESSLER.

03:44.325 --> 03:46.427
LET'S HEAR IT.

03:46.427 --> 03:47.961
[CLEARS THROAT]

03:47.961 --> 03:48.962
CHAPTER ONE...

03:48.962 --> 03:49.963
FROM MEMORY?

03:49.963 --> 03:51.198
YES, SIR.

03:51.198 --> 03:53.967
I DON'T KNOW WHETHER
THAT DENOTES HARD WORK

03:53.967 --> 03:56.103
OR UNSEEMLY VANITY.

03:56.103 --> 03:57.571
STAND UP.

03:58.739 --> 03:59.740
STAND UP?

03:59.740 --> 04:02.976
I LIKE
A SUBSTANTIAL TARGET.

04:08.382 --> 04:10.618
CHAPTER ONE...

04:10.618 --> 04:13.287
THE BOTTOMLESS WELL
OF NEED.

04:13.287 --> 04:14.788
THE NOBLE AND AMBITIOUS
ASSUMPTION

04:14.788 --> 04:17.391
OF THE GOVERNMENT
OF THE UNITED STATES

04:17.391 --> 04:19.993
IS THAT THE NEEDS
OF A DIVERSE POPULATION

04:19.993 --> 04:21.595
CAN BE FULFILLED.

04:21.595 --> 04:25.132
THE DREAM OF A MELTING POT
HAS BECOME A CAULDRON

04:25.132 --> 04:28.135
OF INFLEXIBLE MINORITIES
AND THE HOPELESSLY
UNEMPLOYABLE.

04:28.135 --> 04:32.340
THE SOLUTION IS
TO LEAVE THE COMPLEXITIES
OF MODERN GOVERNMENT

04:32.340 --> 04:33.874
TO THE POLITICAL EXPERT--

04:33.874 --> 04:34.708
[SNIFF SNIFF]

04:34.708 --> 04:37.244
AND TO RETHINK
OUR NAIVE FAITH

04:37.244 --> 04:39.279
IN THE WISDOM
OF THE PEOPLE.

04:39.279 --> 04:41.014
A GOOD BEGINNING.

04:41.014 --> 04:42.650
LEAVE YOUR CHAPTER.

04:42.650 --> 04:44.652
IF THE REST
OF YOUR THESIS

04:44.652 --> 04:46.253
IS AS INTELLIGENT
AS YOU ARE,

04:46.253 --> 04:48.822
YOU ARE CERTAIN
TO GRADUATE

04:48.822 --> 04:50.223
SUMMA CUM LAUDE.

04:50.223 --> 04:52.493
AND THAT WILL BE
THE BEGINNING

04:52.493 --> 04:56.464
OF A BRILLIANT CAREER.

04:57.365 --> 04:59.533
THANK YOU,
PROFESSOR PITKANNAN.

05:03.537 --> 05:07.140
DO YOU THINK HELGA
IS A VOLUPTUOUS
SAINT-EMILION

05:07.140 --> 05:09.377
OR A BUTTERY CHARDONNAY?

05:09.377 --> 05:11.379
YOU MEAN HELGA
WITH THE COILS,

05:11.379 --> 05:13.381
WORKS OVER
AT KINKO COPY?

05:13.381 --> 05:15.383
[BROOKLYN ACCENT]
YEAH, DAT'S HER.

05:15.383 --> 05:16.384
WHADDYA THINK?

05:16.384 --> 05:18.852
WHAT DO I THINK?
BUD LITE.

05:18.852 --> 05:20.320
IT'S NOT FUNNY.

05:20.320 --> 05:21.722
MONTY. I'D
APPRECIATE IT

05:21.722 --> 05:23.724
IF YOU WOULDN'T
START YOUR DAY

05:23.724 --> 05:25.058
BY DEMORALIZING
MY CREW.

05:25.058 --> 05:27.861
COURTNEY, YOU'RE JUST
NOT A LEADER OF MEN.

05:27.861 --> 05:28.862
VERY FUNNY.

05:28.862 --> 05:30.263
THEN BE A MODEL.

05:30.263 --> 05:31.865
HEY,
HEY, HEY.

05:31.865 --> 05:33.266
MONTY, HOW'D IT GO?

05:33.266 --> 05:34.668
HOW DID WHAT GO?

05:34.668 --> 05:37.671
THE BIG MEETING
WITH THE GOD
OF YOUR IDOLATRY.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.272
PITKANNAN.
IT WENT GREAT.

05:39.272 --> 05:40.408
RAH.

05:40.408 --> 05:42.275
YOU CAN'T SIT DOWN
FOR FIVE SECONDS?

05:42.275 --> 05:43.477
THE BEST NEVER
REST, JEFF.

05:43.477 --> 05:45.078
I HATE HIM.

05:45.078 --> 05:46.880
HE IS A TAD COMPULSIVE.

05:46.880 --> 05:49.282
HE HAS TO BE.
HARVARD'S NOT
HIS INHERITANCE.

05:49.282 --> 05:51.885
IT'S TRUE. HARVARD
DOESN'T HAVE ANY
STANDARDS LEFT.

05:51.885 --> 05:54.187
THEY LET IN
ANYONE WHO'S BRIGHT.

05:54.187 --> 05:55.656
I'M WORRIED ABOUT HIM.

05:55.656 --> 05:58.659
OH, YEAH.
THE POOR GUY'S THE PET
OF A NOBEL LAUREATE.

05:58.659 --> 06:01.762
PITKANNAN SPENDS
MORE TIME ON NIGHTLINE
THAN IN LECTURE HALLS.

06:01.762 --> 06:04.331
HE'S A CELEBRITY,
NOT AN INTELLECTUAL.

06:04.331 --> 06:06.600
HE'LL STILL GET MONTY
INTO GRADUATE SCHOOL

06:06.600 --> 06:08.335
AND SET HIM UP FOR LIFE.

06:08.335 --> 06:09.803
SOUNDS LIKE
A DEATH SENTENCE.

06:25.218 --> 06:27.220
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

06:27.220 --> 06:29.557
OH, SHIT.

06:35.963 --> 06:38.098
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

06:40.167 --> 06:41.401
NO.

06:44.738 --> 06:46.840
NO. NO.

06:46.840 --> 06:48.809
NO!

06:49.977 --> 06:51.945
MONTY!

06:55.716 --> 06:57.885
YOUR HARD DRIVE
IS FRIED.

06:57.885 --> 06:59.086
O.K.

07:02.222 --> 07:03.691
YOU'VE DONE
10 CHAPTERS ALREADY?

07:03.691 --> 07:05.693
I'M GOING
TO GET XEROXES.

07:05.693 --> 07:07.260
JUST WAIT TILL MORNING.

07:07.260 --> 07:08.762
IT'S MY ONLY COPY.

07:08.762 --> 07:12.065
YOU'RE AFRAID
SOMEONE'S GOING TO
BREAK IN AND STEAL IT?

07:12.065 --> 07:14.668
I CAN'T TAKE CHANCES.
THIS IS MY LIFE.

07:14.668 --> 07:16.303
IT'S NOT YOUR LIFE.

07:16.303 --> 07:17.738
I'M GOING WITH HIM.

07:17.738 --> 07:18.739
GOOD.

07:43.096 --> 07:44.898
MONTY, WAIT UP!

07:44.898 --> 07:46.967
I DIDN'T ASK YOU
TO TAG ALONG.

07:46.967 --> 07:49.302
YOU'RE WELCOME,
YOU BASTARD.

07:49.302 --> 07:51.471
YOU JUST CAN'T
KEEP UP WITH ME.

07:53.040 --> 07:56.409
[LAUGHING]

07:56.409 --> 08:01.281
AW, MONTY.
ARE YOU O.K.?

08:01.281 --> 08:04.184
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:04.184 --> 08:06.654
OH, GOOD.
IT'S DOWN THERE.

08:06.654 --> 08:08.856
IN THE BOILER ROOM?

08:08.856 --> 08:11.458
I GOT TO GET
INTO WIDENER.

08:11.458 --> 08:13.060
IT'S CLOSED.
WAIT TILL MORNING.

08:13.060 --> 08:14.361
I CAN'T WAIT--OHH.

08:14.361 --> 08:15.596
YOU'RE HURT.

08:15.596 --> 08:19.833
MONTY...WOULD YOU
LIKE MY HELP GETTING IN?

08:22.435 --> 08:24.371
YES.

08:24.371 --> 08:26.940
SINCE YOU ASKED
SO NICELY...

08:26.940 --> 08:28.676
COME ON.

08:29.743 --> 08:31.344
THROUGH THE FRONT DOOR?

08:31.344 --> 08:33.780
YES. I KNOW THE GUARD.

08:36.616 --> 08:38.619
HI, CHUCK.

08:38.619 --> 08:41.221
IT'S KIND OF LATE.
YOU O.K.?

08:41.221 --> 08:43.023
YEAH. I WAS HERE
EARLIER,

08:43.023 --> 08:45.626
AND I THINK
I MISPLACED MY WALLET.

08:45.626 --> 08:47.160
DID ANYONE TURN IT IN?

08:47.160 --> 08:49.763
I DON'T REMEMBER
ANYBODY BRINGING IN
A WALLET,

08:49.763 --> 08:52.365
BUT LET ME
TAKE A LOOK.

08:52.365 --> 08:54.768
OH, I FOUND
A HAT HERE

08:54.768 --> 08:58.305
AND, UH, A SCARF.

08:58.305 --> 09:00.407
I GOT A BANANA.

09:00.407 --> 09:02.409
WHAT COLOR
WAS THAT WALLET?

09:02.409 --> 09:04.812
UM, IT WAS GREEN.
ALLIGATOR GREEN.

09:04.812 --> 09:08.081
ALLIGATOR GREEN. WELL,
THAT'S KIND OF SPIFFY. HEH.

09:50.290 --> 09:51.591
[HISS]
OW!

10:02.035 --> 10:04.037
[COUGHS]

10:34.401 --> 10:36.904
NO! NO!

10:38.171 --> 10:40.908
HEY! STOP.
I'M JUST A STUDENT!

10:40.908 --> 10:44.111
HEY, WILL YOU JUST
CALM DOWN? OW!

10:44.111 --> 10:45.512
AH!

10:45.512 --> 10:46.513
IT'S MINE.

10:46.513 --> 10:47.848
THAT'S ALL I WANT.

10:47.848 --> 10:50.684
IT'S IMPORTANT.
IT BELONGS TO ME.

10:50.684 --> 10:53.420
FINDERS, KEEPERS.
LOSERS, WEEPERS.

10:53.420 --> 10:56.523
DON'T YOU KNOCK
BEFORE COMING
INTO SOMEONE'S HOME?

10:56.523 --> 10:57.891
IT'S NOT WORTH ANYTHING.

10:57.891 --> 11:00.627
THEN WHY
WOULD YOU WANT IT?

11:00.627 --> 11:02.662
O.K., HOW MUCH?

11:02.662 --> 11:04.865
I'VE GOT A CHECK.

11:04.865 --> 11:06.666
IS IT CERTIFIED?
HOW ABOUT A CD?

11:06.666 --> 11:09.903
I NEED SOMETHING
I CAN CHEW, KID.

11:09.903 --> 11:12.505
O.K. YOU WANT FOOD?
I'LL BRING YOU SOME.

11:12.505 --> 11:14.875
THEN YOU GIVE ME THAT.

11:14.875 --> 11:16.810
WHAT SIZE UNDERPANTS
YOU WEAR?

11:16.810 --> 11:18.611
EXCUSE ME?

11:18.611 --> 11:20.948
WHAT SIZE
ARE YOUR UNDERPANTS?

11:20.948 --> 11:22.750
I'LL BRING YOU
SOME UNDERPANTS.

11:22.750 --> 11:24.785
JUST DON'T BURN
ANY MORE PAGES.

11:24.785 --> 11:27.587
I'LL BRING UNDERPANTS,
YOU GIVE MY THESIS BACK.

11:27.587 --> 11:31.624
IS THAT WHAT THIS
PIECE OF SHIT'S
SUPPOSED TO BE?

11:31.624 --> 11:34.227
WHAT'S IT SUPPOSED
TO BE ON, HARVARD?

11:34.227 --> 11:35.829
GOVERNMENT.

11:35.829 --> 11:37.831
GOVERNMENT? I DIDN'T
RECOGNIZE YOU.

11:37.831 --> 11:39.266
YOU'RE DAN QUAYLE.

11:39.266 --> 11:42.235
YOU CAME BACK TO FINISH
YOUR EDUCATION,
HUH, BOY?

11:42.235 --> 11:45.238
YOU STUDY GOVERNMENT,
SO THIS SHOULD BE EASY.

11:45.238 --> 11:47.440
YOU WANT SOMETHING?
I NEED SOMETHING.

11:47.440 --> 11:49.509
GO GET ME
A GLAZED DOUGHNUT.

11:49.509 --> 11:51.278
A GLAZED DOUGHNUT.

11:51.278 --> 11:53.646
MAKE SURE THE GLAZE
IS NOT ALL BROKE.

11:53.646 --> 11:55.015
WHAT ABOUT
YOUR UNDERPANTS?

11:55.015 --> 11:57.117
WHAT ABOUT
MY UNDERPANTS?

11:57.117 --> 11:58.051
THE--

11:58.051 --> 12:00.520
CLEAN UNDERPANTS, TOO.
THAT'S RIGHT.

12:00.520 --> 12:01.922
FINE. GREAT.
GLAZED DOUGHNUT--

12:01.922 --> 12:03.190
PRISTINE
GLAZED DOUGHNUT.

12:03.190 --> 12:06.193
PRISTINE GLAZED DOUGHNUT
AND UNDERPANTS.

12:06.193 --> 12:07.460
WHAT DO I GET?

12:07.460 --> 12:08.929
FOR EACH THING
YOU GIVE,

12:08.929 --> 12:11.098
I'LL GIVE YOU
ONE THING.

12:11.098 --> 12:11.899
A CHAPTER.

12:11.899 --> 12:14.334
NO. A PAGE
IS A THING.

12:14.334 --> 12:16.569
A CHAPTER
IS A WHOLE LOT
OF THINGS.

12:16.569 --> 12:19.372
THERE ARE 88 PAGES
IN THAT THESIS.

12:19.372 --> 12:22.876
THERE ARE 83 PAGES NOW.

12:26.079 --> 12:29.749
I FOUND A WAY TO LIVE
THROUGH THE WINTER,
HARVARD.

12:38.691 --> 12:40.493
I HOPE YOU GOT IT,

12:40.493 --> 12:44.697
BECAUSE I JUST WENT
THROUGH TWO YEARS
OF LOST AND FOUND.

12:44.697 --> 12:46.699
YOU DIDN'T GET IT?

12:46.699 --> 12:47.935
OOH. AH!

12:47.935 --> 12:51.171
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GET YOU
TO THE INFIRMARY.

12:53.340 --> 12:54.141
PERFECT.

12:54.141 --> 12:57.477
THE GLAZE
IS ALMOST PERFECT.

12:57.477 --> 12:58.846
THERE'S NO POINT.

12:58.846 --> 13:00.247
I'M CALLING
THE UNIVERSITY COPS.

13:00.247 --> 13:02.715
LET'S NEGOTIATE.
HOW MUCH CASH
DO WE HAVE?

13:02.715 --> 13:03.851
CAN'T EAT MONEY.

13:03.851 --> 13:05.352
DOESN'T MONEY BUY FOOD?

13:05.352 --> 13:06.186
HELGA...

13:06.186 --> 13:07.787
YOU'RE BRILLIANT.
I LOVE YOU.

13:07.787 --> 13:09.289
HE'S PROBABLY
SCHIZOPHRENIC.

13:09.289 --> 13:12.425
MOST OF THE HOMELESS
ARE SCHIZOPHRENICS
OFF MEDICATION.

13:12.425 --> 13:13.726
I HAVE 50 ON ME.

13:13.726 --> 13:16.129
I NEED THE MONEY
TO FIX THE COMPUTER.

13:16.129 --> 13:18.131
IF I CONVINCE
MY ESTEEMED FATHER

13:18.131 --> 13:20.133
THAT THE MONEY
ISN'T FOR ME, MAYBE--

13:20.133 --> 13:21.601
EVERETT,
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

13:21.601 --> 13:25.105
THIS GUY COULD BE
USING MY THESIS
FOR TOILET PAPER.

13:25.105 --> 13:27.107
HE COULD BE EATING IT.

13:27.107 --> 13:28.909
HE HAS NO RESPECT
FOR HIMSELF,

13:28.909 --> 13:31.278
MUCH LESS FOR WHAT
I'M STRUGGLING TO DO.

13:31.278 --> 13:34.281
HE LIKED TORMENTING ME.
HE WANTS ME TO FAIL.

13:34.281 --> 13:36.383
PITKANNAN ADVISED
BILL RAPP LAST YEAR.

13:36.383 --> 13:38.285
HE DROPPED HIM
JUST BEFORE DEADLINE

13:38.285 --> 13:40.520
BECAUSE HE DIDN'T
HAVE A ROUGH DRAFT.

13:40.520 --> 13:41.354
OH, GOD.

13:41.354 --> 13:43.290
YOU NEED REST.
GET SOME SLEEP.

13:43.290 --> 13:45.292
WE'LL GET A FRESH
DOUGHNUT TOMORROW.

13:45.292 --> 13:48.495
I'M SURE HE DOESN'T
WANT YOU TO FAIL.

13:48.495 --> 13:49.897
JUST REASON
WITH HIM.

13:49.897 --> 13:52.299
DEAL WITH HIM
LIKE A HUMAN BEING.

13:52.299 --> 13:55.302
I KNOW HE'S A HUMAN BEING.
I SMELLED HIM.

13:55.302 --> 13:57.905
HE'S A WORTHLESS, STINKING,
FILTHY, USELESS HUMAN BEING.

13:57.905 --> 14:01.208
YEAH. HELLO. SECURITY?

14:03.776 --> 14:06.113
WATCH YOUR STEP THERE.

14:08.215 --> 14:09.616
YOU BUNCH
OF SCAVENGERS.

14:09.616 --> 14:13.253
THANKS FOR
THE DOUGHNUT,
YOU LITTLE STOOLIE.

14:13.253 --> 14:15.255
COME ON.

14:15.255 --> 14:17.457
HEY, MONTY,
IS THAT HIM?

14:17.457 --> 14:19.226
HE'S A LITTLE OLD MAN.

14:19.226 --> 14:22.229
OFFICER, IT ISN'T HERE.
NOW WHERE IS IT?

14:22.229 --> 14:26.033
IT'S NOT DOWN THERE,
AND IT'S NOT ON HIM.

14:27.334 --> 14:28.535
[GAVEL POUNDS]

14:29.836 --> 14:31.838
YOU'VE ALL BEEN
IN VIOLATION

14:31.838 --> 14:33.240
OF CAMBRIDGE
CITY ORDINANCES

14:33.240 --> 14:35.842
AND ARE CHARGED
WITH PUBLIC INTOXICATION

14:35.842 --> 14:37.210
AND/OR VAGRANCY
AND/OR PANHANDLING.

14:37.210 --> 14:39.846
IF YOU PLEAD GUILTY,
PLEASE SIT DOWN.

14:39.846 --> 14:43.050
IF YOU PLEAD NOT GUILTY,
STEP FORWARD.

14:44.284 --> 14:45.818
NAME?

14:45.818 --> 14:47.220
SIMON B. WILDER, JUDGE.

14:47.220 --> 14:51.058
AS A TAXPAYER, I'D LIKE
TO REQUEST A TRIAL BY JURY.

14:51.058 --> 14:53.961
AND WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU PAID TAXES?

14:53.961 --> 14:55.828
THREE TIMES
JUST LAST WEEK.

14:55.828 --> 14:57.364
YOU PAID TAXES THREE TIMES?

14:57.364 --> 14:58.531
YES, SIR.

14:58.531 --> 15:02.102
THERE'S A FEDERAL, STATE,
AND COUNTY TAX ON WINE.

15:03.903 --> 15:06.906
MR. WILDER, THE COURT
CONCEDES THAT YOU HAVE

15:06.906 --> 15:08.308
PAID VARIOUS TAXES.

15:08.308 --> 15:11.378
NEVERTHELESS, A JURY TRIAL
IS NOT CALLED FOR.

15:11.378 --> 15:13.380
THE CHARGES OF PUBLIC
DRUNKENNESS,

15:13.380 --> 15:15.115
TRESPASSING, AND VAGRANCY
STILL STAND.

15:15.115 --> 15:16.716
HOW DO YOU PLEAD?

15:16.716 --> 15:17.985
NOT GUILTY.

15:17.985 --> 15:20.320
YOU WERE FOUND LIVING
IN AN OLD FURNACE ROOM

15:20.320 --> 15:22.922
UNDER WIDENER LIBRARY ON
THE HARVARD COLLEGE CAMPUS.

15:22.922 --> 15:24.224
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,

15:24.224 --> 15:26.793
HARVARD UNIVERSITY
IS A LAND-GRANT SCHOOL.

15:26.793 --> 15:29.562
CONSTITUTIONALLY,
I WAS LIVING
ON PUBLIC GROUNDS.

15:29.562 --> 15:32.165
I'LL DROP THE CHARGE
OF TRESPASSING,

15:32.165 --> 15:34.968
BUT YOUR BREATHALYZER TEST
SHOWED YOU WERE DRUNK

15:34.968 --> 15:36.403
WHEN YOU WERE ARRESTED.

15:36.403 --> 15:39.172
AT MY ARREST,
I WAS NEITHER
DRIVING AN AUTOMOBILE

15:39.172 --> 15:41.374
OR OPERATING
HEAVY FARM EQUIPMENT.

15:41.374 --> 15:43.443
I WAS READING.
I'M PAST
THE DRINKING AGE.

15:43.443 --> 15:46.179
IF I DRINK TO KILL
THE WINTER CHILL,

15:46.179 --> 15:47.680
IT'S NOT A CRIME.

15:47.680 --> 15:51.184
IF IT WERE, EVERY FAN
AT A HARVARD/YALE
FOOTBALL GAME

15:51.184 --> 15:53.420
WOULD BE BEHIND BARS.
COME ON!

15:53.420 --> 15:55.222
[GAVEL POUNDS]

15:55.222 --> 15:56.956
BE CAREFUL, MR. WILDER.

15:56.956 --> 15:58.558
YOU'RE COMING
DANGEROUSLY CLOSE

15:58.558 --> 15:59.759
TO CONTEMPT OF COURT.

15:59.759 --> 16:02.862
I'LL DROP THE CHARGES
OF PUBLIC INTOXICATION.

16:02.862 --> 16:04.264
THANK YOU, YOUR HONOR.

16:04.264 --> 16:05.865
YOU'RE A GENTLEMAN
AND A SCHOLAR.

16:05.865 --> 16:08.201
I KNEW WE'D
HIT IT OFF FAMOUSLY.

16:08.201 --> 16:10.203
WHEN I HEARD
THAT PHONY ACCENT,

16:10.203 --> 16:13.006
I THOUGHT HE WAS
GOING TO BE AN ASSHOLE.

16:13.006 --> 16:14.374
JUST GOES TO SHOW--

16:14.374 --> 16:17.010
THAT'S IT, MR. WILDER.
I'M HOLDING YOU IN CONTEMPT.

16:17.010 --> 16:18.411
$50 OR 50 DAYS.

16:18.411 --> 16:20.413
YOU'LL BE HEARING
FROM ALAN DERSHOWITZ.

16:20.413 --> 16:22.815
LET'S SEE HOW
YOU DO WITH HIM!

16:22.815 --> 16:24.151
MAY I PAY THAT FINE?

16:24.151 --> 16:26.419
ARE YOU RELATED
TO MR. WILDER?

16:26.419 --> 16:28.621
NO, SIR.
I'M A HARVARD STUDENT.

16:28.621 --> 16:29.856
I'M WRITING MY THESIS,

16:29.856 --> 16:31.858
AND I NEED
MR. WILDER'S HELP.

16:31.858 --> 16:33.660
THIS YOUNG MAN
WILL PAY THE FINE,

16:33.660 --> 16:36.829
PROVIDED HE GETS MR. WILDER
OUT OF MY SIGHT.

16:36.829 --> 16:38.231
NEXT CASE, PLEASE.

16:38.231 --> 16:40.467
DON'T ASK HIM
FOR A GLAZED DOUGHNUT.

16:40.467 --> 16:42.135
[LAUGHTER]

16:49.676 --> 16:51.078
EXCUSE ME, MISS.

16:51.078 --> 16:53.080
CAN I BORROW YOUR QUARTER?

16:53.080 --> 16:55.782
I'D LIKE TO GET
THE MORNING PAPER.

16:55.782 --> 16:57.384
THANK YOU, SWEETHEART.

16:57.384 --> 17:00.853
YOU KNOW WHAT THE GREATEST
NATION IN THE WORLD IS,
DON'T YOU?

17:00.853 --> 17:02.755
I HOPE IT'S THE USA.

17:02.755 --> 17:04.156
WRONG. IT'S DO-NATION.

17:04.156 --> 17:05.758
HERE YOU GO.

17:05.758 --> 17:07.560
THAT'S FOR BEING
SO GENEROUS.

17:07.560 --> 17:10.262
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME
FOR YOUR FRIENDS?

17:10.262 --> 17:11.864
NO. ONE'S FINE.
THANKS.

17:11.864 --> 17:13.266
THANK YOU.
BYE, SWEETHEART.

17:13.266 --> 17:16.035
MR. WILDER, I HAVE
A BUSINESS PROPOSITION.

17:16.035 --> 17:17.337
I THINK THAT--

17:17.337 --> 17:19.939
BUY THE BOSTON HERALD
OVER HERE!

17:19.939 --> 17:21.340
ONLY 25 CENTS!

17:21.340 --> 17:24.277
GET YOUR PAPER
OVER HERE.
ONLY 25 CENTS!

17:24.277 --> 17:25.877
READ ALL ABOUT IT.

17:25.877 --> 17:27.280
CLARENCE THOMAS
WINS APPOINTMENT.

17:27.280 --> 17:29.882
MOVES IN ON TOP
OF HILL.

17:29.882 --> 17:31.751
I'LL TAKE ONE OF THOSE.

17:31.751 --> 17:34.020
LET ME
CHECK THAT OUT.

17:34.020 --> 17:35.021
25 CENTS.

17:35.021 --> 17:36.623
IT'S ON PAGE FIVE.

17:36.623 --> 17:38.024
I BAILED YOU OUT.

17:38.024 --> 17:40.627
I THINK THAT ENTITLES ME
TO A CONVERSATION.

17:40.627 --> 17:42.028
READ ALL ABOUT IT!

17:42.028 --> 17:44.631
HARVARD STUDENT
DIES IN FREAK ACCIDENT!

17:44.631 --> 17:46.433
CRUSHED BY GIANT EGO.

17:46.433 --> 17:49.969
I'LL TAKE THE REST.
HERE'S 5 BUCKS.

17:49.969 --> 17:52.972
WHAT DO YOU SEE
WHEN YOU LOOK AT ME?

17:52.972 --> 17:54.073
A MAN.

17:54.073 --> 17:56.109
YOU SEE A PIECE
OF SHIT, HARVARD.

17:56.109 --> 17:58.311
I SEE A MAN
WHO NEEDS A HOME.

17:58.311 --> 18:01.914
I HAD A HOME. I HAD
A WARM PLACE TO SLEEP...

18:01.914 --> 18:03.916
17 BATHROOMS
AND 8 MILES OF BOOKS.

18:03.916 --> 18:05.918
I HAD A GODDAMN PALACE.

18:05.918 --> 18:07.720
YOU KNOW WHY
I NEED A HOME?

18:07.720 --> 18:09.122
'CAUSE OF YOU.

18:09.122 --> 18:11.191
'CAUSE WHEN YOU
LOOKED AT ME,

18:11.191 --> 18:13.460
YOU DIDN'T SEE A MAN.

18:20.767 --> 18:21.801
WELL?

18:27.774 --> 18:30.177
WHAT'S THAT?

18:31.678 --> 18:32.745
A HOUSE.

18:35.114 --> 18:36.216
I'D PREFER THAT.

18:36.216 --> 18:37.217
IT'S FULL.

18:37.217 --> 18:39.819
IT'S THE BEST
I CAN DO.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.358
MY ROOMMATE BOZ
CRACKED UP
TWO MONTHS AGO

18:45.358 --> 18:46.759
AND QUIT SCHOOL.

18:46.759 --> 18:47.960
THIS IS HIS STUFF.

18:47.960 --> 18:49.562
WHERE IS HE NOW?

18:49.562 --> 18:50.363
BALI.

18:50.363 --> 18:52.365
BALI? I'VE BEEN THERE.

18:52.365 --> 18:53.966
MERCHANT MARINES.

18:53.966 --> 18:56.203
SWAB THE DECKS
AND SEE THE WORLD.

18:56.203 --> 18:58.070
JUST DON'T BREATHE
IN THE ENGINE ROOM.

18:58.070 --> 19:00.340
WELL, ALL THIS
COMFORT CAN BE YOURS

19:00.340 --> 19:01.941
FOR JUST
ONE SENIOR THESIS.

19:01.941 --> 19:03.243
FOR EACH NIGHT'S LODGING,

19:03.243 --> 19:04.411
ONE PAGE.

19:04.411 --> 19:06.613
LOOK, I DON'T THINK
YOU UNDERSTAND.

19:06.613 --> 19:09.482
THIS IS NINE MONTHS
OF MY WORK.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.484
GIVE ME
ALL THE PAGES NOW,

19:11.484 --> 19:13.386
AND YOU CAN STAY
UNTIL SPRING.

19:13.386 --> 19:14.654
YOU HAVE MY WORD.

19:14.654 --> 19:17.624
YOUR WORD, HARVARD?
SURELY, YE JEST.

19:17.624 --> 19:20.227
DID YOU FORGET
ABOUT OUR ORIGINAL DEAL?

19:20.227 --> 19:22.229
ONE THING FOR ONE THING.

19:22.229 --> 19:23.630
GET A LITTLE CREATIVE,

19:23.630 --> 19:26.633
YOU'LL HAVE ME OUT
IN NO TIME.

19:26.633 --> 19:29.436
BY THE WAY,

19:29.436 --> 19:31.404
I'LL NEED SOMETHING
DECENT TO READ.

19:31.404 --> 19:33.506
TAKE ANYTHING YOU WANT
FROM THE LIBRARY.

19:33.506 --> 19:36.108
WELL, I WAS READING
GERMINAL BY ZOLA

19:36.108 --> 19:38.511
TILL I WAS
SO RUDELY INTERRUPTED.

19:38.511 --> 19:40.913
YOU'LL HAVE IT
BY TOMORROW.

19:40.913 --> 19:42.982
BOY, OH, BOY.

19:42.982 --> 19:44.384
WHERE YOU GOING?

19:44.384 --> 19:46.253
GOT TO GET
DINNER, HARVARD.

19:46.253 --> 19:48.255
MY ROOMMATES
ARE COOKING DINNER.

19:48.255 --> 19:50.223
I'LL GET YOU SOME.

19:50.223 --> 19:51.824
WAIT A MINUTE.

19:51.824 --> 19:53.226
WHAT ARE THEY HAVING?

19:53.226 --> 19:55.295
WHAT ARE THEY HAVING?

19:58.798 --> 20:01.000
HELLO, SPEEDY.

20:01.000 --> 20:02.602
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

20:03.403 --> 20:05.004
THAT GOOD, HUH?

20:05.004 --> 20:06.239
CHECK THAT FOR YOU?

20:06.239 --> 20:07.507
MR. ONE-CRUTCH
MAN!

20:07.507 --> 20:09.876
DIDN'T THE DOCTOR SAY
TO USE BOTH CRUTCHES?

20:09.876 --> 20:11.278
I ONLY NEED ONE.

20:11.278 --> 20:13.280
DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE EVEN AFRAID

20:13.280 --> 20:15.282
TO DEPEND ON
INANIMATE OBJECTS.

20:15.282 --> 20:17.284
ANYONE MIND
IF I HAVE SECONDS?

20:17.284 --> 20:19.286
I'LL KICK IN EXTRA
FOR GROCERIES.

20:19.286 --> 20:21.288
YOU STILL OWE
FOR LAST WEEK.

20:21.288 --> 20:24.291
I'M GOOD FOR IT.
CAN YOU GET THE DOOR?

20:24.291 --> 20:26.693
ARE YOU DINING
ON THE TERRACE
THIS EVENING?

20:26.693 --> 20:29.929
* YOU WERE IN MY TIME *

20:29.929 --> 20:33.199
* YOU WERE DRIVING
CIRCLES *

20:33.199 --> 20:35.234
* AROUND ME... **

20:35.234 --> 20:37.504
THIS MEET
YOUR STANDARDS?

20:39.972 --> 20:41.941
WHEN DO I GET MY PAGE?

20:41.941 --> 20:42.842
TOMORROW.

20:42.842 --> 20:46.313
IF YOU EAT NOW,
I GET MY PAGE NOW.

20:46.313 --> 20:48.315
IF YOU HAD
AN INSURANCE POLICY,

20:48.315 --> 20:49.716
WOULD YOU
CARRY IT AROUND?

20:49.716 --> 20:51.351
YOU'RE BEING
VERY UNREASONABLE.

20:51.351 --> 20:54.186
HOW DO I KNOW
YOU DIDN'T BURN IT?

20:54.186 --> 20:55.588
YOU THINK I'M AN IDIOT?

20:55.588 --> 20:58.325
NO, HARVARD.
I THINK YOU'RE A LOSER.

20:58.325 --> 20:59.659
[DOOR CLOSES]

21:00.793 --> 21:02.795
OH, HI.

21:04.263 --> 21:06.499
FINE.

21:06.499 --> 21:08.535
TOMORROW THEN. FINE.

21:13.139 --> 21:16.208
WHAT IF MY PARENTS
PULL A SURPRISE
WEEKEND VISIT?

21:16.208 --> 21:19.011
MY MOM WOULD HAVE
A HEART ATTACK.

21:19.011 --> 21:22.214
I MEAN, DON'T YOU THINK
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN

21:22.214 --> 21:23.616
A LITTLE MORE CONSIDERATE

21:23.616 --> 21:25.618
IF YOU'D ASKED
JEFF'S MOTHER FIRST?

21:25.618 --> 21:27.354
DON'T LECTURE ME
ABOUT CONSIDERATION.

21:27.354 --> 21:28.588
YOU KEEP A ROOSTER.

21:28.588 --> 21:31.491
MY COCK IS A LOT CLEANER
THAN YOUR BUM.

21:31.491 --> 21:33.360
WE'RE COMPARING
COCKS AND BUMS?

21:33.360 --> 21:35.027
IS THIS INSIDE
MACHO TALK?

21:35.027 --> 21:37.730
THE ROOSTER
IS THE CENTERPIECE
OF MY RADIO SHOW.

21:37.730 --> 21:40.633
FINE. THE BUM
IS THE CENTERPIECE
OF MY LIFE.

21:40.633 --> 21:42.635
DOES ANYBODY
HAVE A RAZOR?

21:42.635 --> 21:45.271
MY LEGS ARE
TURNING INTO
CHRISTMAS TREES.

21:45.271 --> 21:47.640
COURTNEY! EWWW.

21:47.640 --> 21:50.109
COME ON.
WE'RE ALL GUYS HERE.

21:50.109 --> 21:51.243
WHAT'S THE OCCASION?

21:51.243 --> 21:52.645
I GOT A DATE.

21:52.645 --> 21:56.215
PROMISED JONATHAN
I'D MAKE UP
WITH HIM AGAIN.

21:56.215 --> 21:57.784
JONATHAN. THE FACE.

21:57.784 --> 22:00.820
HE'S MORE THAN THAT.
HE'S ALSO A GREAT BODY.

22:00.820 --> 22:03.490
JESUS, COURTNEY.
COULD WE NOT TALK

22:03.490 --> 22:04.791
ABOUT SEX RIGHT NOW?

22:04.791 --> 22:07.394
JEFF, YOU FORGOT TO TAKE
YOUR GIRLFRIEND HOME,

22:07.394 --> 22:08.528
SO I DEFLATED HER.

22:08.528 --> 22:09.896
[MONTY]
TAKE MY BLADE.

22:09.896 --> 22:10.797
THANKS.

22:10.797 --> 22:14.000
REMEMBER, IF YOU
TIRE OF THE FACE,

22:14.000 --> 22:15.868
HELGA'S
GOT A BROTHER.

22:17.904 --> 22:19.506
HOW'S THE VIEW?

22:20.707 --> 22:22.709
THIS ISN'T
GOING TO WORK.

22:22.709 --> 22:25.311
I'VE BEEN WORKING ON THIS
SINCE JUNIOR YEAR.

22:25.311 --> 22:27.313
I'M NOT GOING
TO START AGAIN

22:27.313 --> 22:29.682
BECAUSE SOME BUM
WANTS TO HOLD IT HOSTAGE.

22:29.682 --> 22:32.852
I'LL TALK HIM INTO
GIVING ME THE WHOLE THING.

22:32.852 --> 22:35.388
YOU'VE BEEN GREAT
AT TALKING HIM
INTO THINGS.

22:35.388 --> 22:37.557
YOU SAID
HE WANTS A HOME.

22:37.557 --> 22:39.426
EVERETT,
I'LL HANDLE IT, O.K.?

22:39.426 --> 22:40.493
O.K., JEFF?

22:40.493 --> 22:42.629
I'LL HAVE HIM OUT
IN A FEW DAYS.

22:42.629 --> 22:44.130
CUT ME SOME SLACK.

22:44.130 --> 22:45.832
[COURTNEY]
MONTY!

22:45.832 --> 22:46.633
MONTY!

22:46.633 --> 22:48.468
KEEP AN EYE ON HIM.

22:48.468 --> 22:52.238
MONTY. MONTY.

22:52.238 --> 22:53.506
GO GET HER, MONTY.

22:53.506 --> 22:55.575
GO GET HER!

22:55.575 --> 22:58.244
I THINK WE SHOULD
CALL YOUR MOTHER.

22:58.244 --> 22:59.846
[SHOWER RUNNING]

23:03.249 --> 23:05.251
HE'S GOING TO FREEZE
OUT THERE.

23:05.251 --> 23:06.886
GIVE HIM MY EXTRA BLANKETS.

23:06.886 --> 23:09.489
I DON'T WANT HIM
TO BE TOO COMFORTABLE.

23:09.489 --> 23:10.857
HE COULD DIE.

23:10.857 --> 23:11.924
NO SUCH LUCK.

23:11.924 --> 23:14.527
YOU'RE NOT REALLY
LIKE THIS, ARE YOU?

23:14.527 --> 23:17.129
TELL ME THIS HARD-HEARTED
JERK ISN'T YOU.

23:17.129 --> 23:18.230
GIVE UP ON ME.

23:18.230 --> 23:19.499
I'M TIRED OF
DISAPPOINTING YOU.

23:19.499 --> 23:21.267
THEN DO IT FOR YOURSELF.

23:21.267 --> 23:23.970
YOU WANT TO BE
A HOT-SHIT DIPLOMAT.

23:23.970 --> 23:25.371
SECRETARY OF STATE?

23:25.371 --> 23:27.674
EVEN PITKANNAN
WOULD OFFER A HOSTILE POWER

23:27.674 --> 23:29.375
BLANKETS
TO ESTABLISH GOOD WILL.

23:29.375 --> 23:30.877
DON'T CUT YOURSELF.

23:35.281 --> 23:37.684
I NEVER WANTED
TO BE A RAZOR

23:37.684 --> 23:39.886
SO BAD IN MY LIFE.

23:52.932 --> 23:54.400
HERE.

23:54.400 --> 23:55.968
IT'S YOUR NAMESAKE'S WORK.

23:55.968 --> 23:57.970
SOMEBODY SPOTTED YOU
IN THE LIBRARY,

23:57.970 --> 24:01.373
THOUGHT YOU WERE
WALT WHITMAN'S GHOST.

24:01.373 --> 24:02.575
BOO.

24:03.710 --> 24:05.845
VAN'S ACTUALLY MINE,
YOU KNOW.

24:05.845 --> 24:08.447
I LOANED MY EX-ROOMMATE
A SMALL FORTUNE...

24:08.447 --> 24:09.716
AND HE FLED TO BALI.

24:09.716 --> 24:11.584
AND I GOT THE VAN.

24:11.584 --> 24:13.219
WHY DON'T YOU SELL IT?

24:13.219 --> 24:14.453
THE ENGINE DOESN'T RUN.

24:14.453 --> 24:17.490
SO FIX IT. WANT ME
TO DO IT FOR YOU?

24:17.490 --> 24:18.991
ARE YOU A MECHANIC?

24:18.991 --> 24:21.127
I'M A ZEN BUDDHIST.
THAT'S CLOSE ENOUGH.

24:21.127 --> 24:24.330
HOW MANY
BOTTLES OF WINE
WOULD YOU GIVE ME

24:24.330 --> 24:26.999
IF I FIXED IT?

24:26.999 --> 24:29.001
SIX.
EIGHT.

24:29.001 --> 24:30.537
EIGHT.
SEVEN.

24:30.537 --> 24:32.204
O.K., NINE.
THAT'S MY FINAL OFFER.

24:32.204 --> 24:35.374
DIDN'T YOU USE TO RUN
A SAVINGS AND LOAN?

24:35.374 --> 24:37.009
YOU'RE THINKING
OF MY FATHER.

24:37.009 --> 24:40.212
LOOK, YOU WANT
A LITTLE SOMETHING
IN ADVANCE?

24:40.212 --> 24:42.014
BOY, OH, BOY.
YOU MUST BE

24:42.014 --> 24:44.517
ONE OF THE GREAT MINDS
OF YOUR GENERATION.

24:44.517 --> 24:46.519
YOU GOT A CORKY SCREW?

24:46.519 --> 24:47.954
[LAUGHING]

26:25.618 --> 26:26.619
HEY, BOY.

26:26.619 --> 26:29.188
HERE WE GO.

26:29.188 --> 26:30.589
FOR LODGINGS AND MEALS,

26:30.589 --> 26:32.992
AND TWO EXTRA
FOR THE BLANKET.

26:32.992 --> 26:33.793
THANKS.

26:33.793 --> 26:35.194
THANKS A LOT,

26:35.194 --> 26:39.165
BUT THE BLANKET WAS JUST,
YOU KNOW, GOODWILL.

26:39.165 --> 26:41.533
GIVE ME YOUR BOOKS.
I'LL CARRY THEM.

26:41.533 --> 26:43.302
WHAT'S THAT GOING
TO COST ME?

26:43.302 --> 26:44.871
IT'S FOR
THE BLANKET, O.K.?

26:44.871 --> 26:47.073
YOU DIDN'T ASK
FOR THE BLANKET,

26:47.073 --> 26:48.975
SO THE BLANKET
DOESN'T COUNT.

26:48.975 --> 26:51.010
I APPRECIATED IT, O.K.?

26:51.010 --> 26:54.847
WOULD YOU APPRECIATE IT
IF I CARRY YOUR BOOKS?

26:57.750 --> 27:00.352
BOY, OH, BOY,
WE'RE IN BUSINESS.

27:04.256 --> 27:05.892
COME ON, BOY.

27:05.892 --> 27:08.695
HIP IT UP, HOPPY.
LET'S GO.

27:09.796 --> 27:12.799
HERE WE ARE,
BACK WHERE YOU FOUND ME.

27:12.799 --> 27:14.200
DON'T REMIND ME.

27:14.200 --> 27:17.403
I WONDER WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO READ UPSTAIRS.

27:17.403 --> 27:19.138
BET THE LIGHT'S BETTER.

28:09.688 --> 28:11.891
GERMINAL, RIGHT?

28:13.960 --> 28:16.963
THIS LIBRARY'S LIKE
A CHURCH, ISN'T IT?

28:16.963 --> 28:20.366
WHEN YOU WERE IN CHURCH,
YOU EVER LOOK UP SOMETIMES

28:20.366 --> 28:22.368
AND WONDER WHAT PEOPLE
WERE PRAYING FOR?

28:22.368 --> 28:24.971
DID SOMEONE DIE?
WAS SOMEONE JUST BORN?

28:24.971 --> 28:26.973
LIBRARY'S LIKE THAT
FOR ME.

28:26.973 --> 28:29.608
SIR. SIR, YOU CAN'T
STAY HERE.

28:29.608 --> 28:31.010
IT'S O.K.
HE'S WITH ME.

28:31.010 --> 28:33.579
HE'S PART OF
MY RESEARCH PROJECT.

28:33.579 --> 28:36.082
OH. I BEG YOUR PARDON.

28:40.352 --> 28:42.421
WOMEN--AIN'T THEY PERFECT?

28:42.421 --> 28:43.255
NOT ALWAYS.

28:43.255 --> 28:44.991
YES, THEY ARE.
THEY'RE PERFECT.

28:44.991 --> 28:47.927
DON'T MATTER
IF THEY'RE SKINNY,
FAT, BLONDE, OR BLUE.

28:47.927 --> 28:50.830
IF A WOMAN'S WILLING
TO GIVE YOU HER LOVE,

28:50.830 --> 28:52.832
IT'S THE GREATEST GIFT
IN THE WORLD.

28:52.832 --> 28:54.834
MAKES YOU TALLER,
MAKES YOU SMARTER,

28:54.834 --> 28:57.804
MAKES YOUR TEETH SHINE.
BOY, WOMEN ARE PERFECT.

28:57.804 --> 28:59.271
KEEP YOUR VOICE LOW.

28:59.271 --> 29:01.707
PERFECT JOY
AND PERFECT ACHE.

29:01.707 --> 29:03.742
JOY WHEN YOU FIRST SEE 'EM,

29:03.742 --> 29:05.744
ACHE WHEN YOU LEAVE 'EM.

29:05.744 --> 29:07.746
JOY. ACHE. JOY. ACHE.

29:07.746 --> 29:10.649
JOY-ACHE, JOY-ACHE,
JOY-ACHE, JOY-ACHE,

29:10.649 --> 29:11.650
JOY-ACHE, JOY-ACHE--

29:11.650 --> 29:12.651
SHH!

29:12.651 --> 29:13.786
IF YOU KEEP
YOUR VOICE LOW,

29:13.786 --> 29:16.522
THEN YOU WOULDN'T
ATTRACT ATTENTION.

29:27.266 --> 29:28.267
PSST.

29:30.937 --> 29:34.140
I'LL GIVE YOU TWO PAGES
FOR A BATH.

29:35.307 --> 29:37.243
UH, O.K.

29:37.243 --> 29:40.012
LET ME GET
SOME WORK DONE.

29:59.866 --> 30:02.534
WHY DID YOU SAY
I WAS A LOSER?

30:02.534 --> 30:03.870
SHH!

30:03.870 --> 30:05.171
TSK TSK TSK.

30:09.441 --> 30:12.845
THE POT CALLING
THE KETTLE BLACK, HUH?

30:14.513 --> 30:17.316
I'M NOT A LOSER, HARVARD.

30:17.316 --> 30:18.717
I'M A QUITTER.

30:18.717 --> 30:21.653
YOU TRY TOO HARD.

30:21.653 --> 30:24.490
WINNERS FORGET
THEY'RE IN A RACE.

30:24.490 --> 30:26.825
THEY JUST LOVE TO RUN.

30:29.028 --> 30:31.430
* MINE EYES HAVE SEEN
THE GLORY *

30:31.430 --> 30:34.366
* OF THE COMING
OF THE LORD *

30:34.366 --> 30:35.367
EVERETT?

30:36.635 --> 30:37.904
EVERETT?

30:37.904 --> 30:40.306
* GRAPES OF WRATH
ARE STORED-- *

30:41.240 --> 30:43.475
* HE HAS LOOSENED UP
THE PANTIES *

30:43.475 --> 30:46.512
* OF THE LITTLE WHORE
NEXT DOOR *

30:46.512 --> 30:49.181
MONTY!

30:50.182 --> 30:54.987
* HIS TRUTH IS
MARCHING ON **

30:55.787 --> 30:56.956
MONT--

30:56.956 --> 30:59.658
O.K., HE CANNOT STAY,
SO GET HIM OUT.

30:59.658 --> 31:01.060
WATER DOESN'T
COST ANYTHING.

31:01.060 --> 31:03.062
I'LL BUY YOU
MORE BUBBLE BATH.

31:03.062 --> 31:06.065
DID YOU GIVE HIM A KEY
TO THE HOUSE?

31:06.065 --> 31:08.467
I SPENT THE DAY WITH HIM.
HE'S HARMLESS.

31:08.467 --> 31:11.070
HE LIKES TO READ.
HE LIKES TO TALK.

31:11.070 --> 31:13.072
I CANNOT TAKE THIS
RIGHT NOW.

31:13.072 --> 31:15.474
I'M NOT GOING TO MAKE
MED SCHOOL, O.K.?

31:15.474 --> 31:18.077
I MADE HARVARD.
I'M NOT MAKING
MED SCHOOL.

31:18.077 --> 31:19.678
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT?

31:19.678 --> 31:21.948
I'VE GOT ONE PAGE
OF MY THESIS.

31:21.948 --> 31:23.682
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

31:23.682 --> 31:25.084
I HEARD YOU PRINTING OUT.

31:25.084 --> 31:27.286
SOUNDED LIKE
YOU HAD 50 PAGES.

31:27.286 --> 31:28.220
BLANKS.

31:28.220 --> 31:29.956
I PRINTED OUT BLANKS.

31:29.956 --> 31:32.824
I DIDN'T WANT
YOU GUYS TO KNOW.

31:32.824 --> 31:34.326
JESUS, JEFF.

31:34.326 --> 31:37.529
AND I THOUGHT
I WAS WOUND TIGHT.

31:37.529 --> 31:40.732
GET HIM OUT.
I CANNOT WORK
WITH HIM AROUND.

31:40.732 --> 31:42.734
WHAT IF MY MOM COMES?

31:42.734 --> 31:44.136
O.K., O.K.
CALM DOWN.

31:44.136 --> 31:46.138
YOU'RE STARTING TO
SOUND LIKE BOZ.

31:46.138 --> 31:47.739
I'M NOTHING
LIKE BOZ.

31:47.739 --> 31:49.141
WHO'S LIKE BOZ?

31:49.141 --> 31:51.710
I THOUGHT BOZ
WAS IN BALI,
BY GOLLY.

31:51.710 --> 31:53.312
HE'S WEARING
MY ROBE.

31:53.312 --> 31:54.113
[SNIFFS]

31:54.113 --> 31:55.847
AND IT SMELLS
TERRIFIC.

31:55.847 --> 31:58.250
I DID LEAVE CLOTHES
OUT FOR YOU.

31:58.250 --> 32:00.252
I CAME DOWN
FOR A BEER.

32:00.252 --> 32:02.788
I CAN'T GET DRESSED
WITHOUT A BEER.

32:02.788 --> 32:03.956
LITTLE QUIRK.

32:03.956 --> 32:06.158
MONTY, THIS IS TOTALLY
OUT OF CONTROL.

32:06.158 --> 32:09.861
YOU WAKE UP
ON THE WRONG SIDE
OF THE BED?

32:09.861 --> 32:10.862
LOVER'S QUARREL?

32:10.862 --> 32:12.264
MAYBE I SHOULD LEAVE.

32:12.264 --> 32:14.266
WE'RE NOT LOVERS.
WE'RE ROOMMATES.

32:14.266 --> 32:15.867
WE RESPECT
EACH OTHER'S SPACE.

32:15.867 --> 32:17.669
YOU RESPECT
EACH OTHER'S EMPTY AIR?

32:17.669 --> 32:20.272
THAT'S VERY PROFOUND
FOR HARVARD STUDENTS.

32:20.272 --> 32:22.474
O.K., LET'S GO. COME ON.

32:22.474 --> 32:23.875
HEY, MY ROBE.

32:23.875 --> 32:26.278
O.K. IF THAT'S HOW
YOU FEEL ABOUT IT,

32:26.278 --> 32:28.247
DON'T LET ME CATCH YOU
WEARING MY THINGS.

32:28.247 --> 32:30.782
JUST KEEP IT, O.K.?

32:30.782 --> 32:31.883
THANK YOU.

32:31.883 --> 32:33.285
BOY, OH, BOY.

32:33.285 --> 32:36.288
THERE'S ENTIRELY
TOO MUCH BICKERING
IN THIS HOUSE.

32:36.288 --> 32:38.690
I DON'T KNOW
IF I COULD LIVE HERE.

32:38.690 --> 32:41.893
I HOPE MY SUMMER PLACE
WILL BE READY SOON.

32:41.893 --> 32:44.463
THEN YOU'LL
PROBABLY MISS ME.

32:44.463 --> 32:47.766
I KNOW, I KNOW.
I HAVE A PLAN.

32:47.766 --> 32:49.568
I'M TAKING HIM
TO SOCIAL SECURITY

32:49.568 --> 32:51.703
AND GETTING HIM
DISABILITY BENEFITS.

32:51.703 --> 32:55.107
WELL, I EXPECT
YOU TO CLEAN
THE BATHTUB.

32:57.409 --> 32:58.510
NAME.

32:58.510 --> 33:00.046
SIMON WILDER.

33:00.046 --> 33:01.447
WHO IS SIMON WILDER?

33:01.447 --> 33:02.848
HE IS.
HE IS.

33:02.848 --> 33:04.883
CUT IT OUT.
HE IS.

33:04.883 --> 33:06.485
ARE YOU SIMON WILDER?

33:06.485 --> 33:07.919
I USED TO BE.

33:07.919 --> 33:09.421
D.O.B.?

33:09.421 --> 33:10.922
E-F-G-H-I-J.

33:10.922 --> 33:13.659
DATE OF BIRTH.

33:13.659 --> 33:15.061
WHEN WERE YOU BORN?

33:15.061 --> 33:17.063
WHEN THE MOON WAS FULL,

33:17.063 --> 33:19.298
I WAS ABANDONED
BY MY MOMMY.

33:19.298 --> 33:23.302
I WAS RAISED
BY A SHE-WOLF
IN A WYOMING CAVE.

33:23.302 --> 33:25.003
THIS WILL
GET YOU MONEY.

33:25.003 --> 33:26.672
YOU NEED MONEY.

33:26.672 --> 33:28.340
I DON'T. YOU DO.

33:28.340 --> 33:31.743
I'LL ASK AGAIN. DO YOU
HAVE EVIDENCE OF BIRTH?

33:31.743 --> 33:33.145
I'M SITTING HERE,
AIN'T I?

33:33.145 --> 33:35.814
DO YOU THINK I HAPPENED
BY SPONTANEOUS COMBUSTION?

33:35.814 --> 33:37.216
HE'S NOT COOPERATING.

33:37.216 --> 33:39.418
WHAT STATE
WERE YOU BORN IN?

33:39.418 --> 33:40.219
INFANCY.

33:40.219 --> 33:41.953
I'M TRYING TO HELP.

33:41.953 --> 33:43.955
YOU SEE THIS FACE,
LADY?

33:43.955 --> 33:45.224
MEMORIZE IT.

33:45.224 --> 33:48.260
SOME DAY THIS BOY'S
GOING TO SAVE THE WORLD.

33:48.260 --> 33:50.596
IF HE'S UNCOOPERATIVE,
THERE'S NOTHING I CAN DO.

33:50.596 --> 33:53.499
I GUESS THAT'S
WHY YOU WORK HERE.

33:53.499 --> 33:56.335
CAN I HAVE ONE OF THESE
MUFFINS, LADY?

33:56.335 --> 33:57.869
NO!

33:57.869 --> 33:59.271
I'M SORRY. UH, NO.

33:59.271 --> 34:01.307
CAN'T EVEN GET
A MUFFIN.

34:01.307 --> 34:04.042
HOW ARE YOU GOING
TO GET CASH?

34:04.042 --> 34:06.445
IF YOU PEOPLE ARE IN LINE
FOR MUFFINS,

34:06.445 --> 34:08.045
YOU'RE WASTING YOUR TIME.

34:08.045 --> 34:10.681
THEY'RE NOT GIVING ANY OUT.

34:10.681 --> 34:13.952
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
WE MADE A DEAL.

34:13.952 --> 34:16.455
I WENT IN,
DIDN'T I?

34:16.455 --> 34:17.889
WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES IT MAKE

34:17.889 --> 34:21.059
WHETHER THE MONEY
COMES FROM ME
OR THE GOVERNMENT?

34:21.059 --> 34:23.462
I GOT A GRIEVANCE
AGAINST THE GOVERNMENT.

34:23.462 --> 34:25.931
YOU PAID
INTO THE SYSTEM.

34:25.931 --> 34:27.333
YOU SAID YOU WORKED--

34:27.333 --> 34:29.235
SAILOR, LUMBERJACK,
SHORT-ORDER COOK.

34:29.235 --> 34:31.137
OR WAS THAT
ALL BULLSHIT?

34:31.137 --> 34:33.339
THERE YOU GO.
EXCUSE ME.

34:37.243 --> 34:41.246
WELL, WE GOING
TO THE MOVIE
OR WHAT?

34:41.246 --> 34:43.849
A DEAL IS A DEAL,
HARVARD.

34:55.393 --> 34:56.795
* KINDA WOMAN *

34:56.795 --> 34:59.798
* I'D GIVE YOU
MY ALL... *

34:59.798 --> 35:02.401
HEY, EVERETT,
CAN I BORROW
SOME CONDOMS?

35:02.401 --> 35:06.004
NO, BUT YOU CAN HAVE SOME.

35:06.004 --> 35:07.005
ENDURANCE TEST?

35:07.005 --> 35:09.040
MORE LIKE
A POP QUIZ.

35:09.040 --> 35:11.009
OH, COURTNEY.

35:11.009 --> 35:12.678
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.

35:12.678 --> 35:14.079
GOOD NIGHT, MONTY.

35:14.079 --> 35:15.681
ARE YOU EXPECTING
AN INVASION?

35:15.681 --> 35:18.284
I DON'T WANT TO BE
MURDERED IN MY BED.

35:18.284 --> 35:22.087
YOUR BED IS THE ONE PLACE
YOU'RE TOTALLY SAFE.

35:22.087 --> 35:23.555
JESUS.

35:28.294 --> 35:31.497
ARE YOU GOING
TO WATCH HIM ALL NIGHT?

35:32.898 --> 35:34.766
LOCKING THE GIRLFRIEND IN?

35:35.967 --> 35:37.569
GOOD NIGHT, LITTLE ONES.

35:37.569 --> 35:42.040
* HAPPINESS,
NO LONGER SAD *

35:42.040 --> 35:44.210
* HAPPINESS *

35:44.210 --> 35:47.513
* I'M GLAD **

35:56.054 --> 35:57.323
OW. OW.

35:57.323 --> 35:58.724
GIVE ME SOME BOOKS.

35:58.724 --> 36:01.527
I'M PERFECTLY CAPABLE
OF CARRYING MY OWN BOOKS,

36:01.527 --> 36:02.528
THANK YOU.

36:09.801 --> 36:11.102
HERE.

36:11.102 --> 36:12.738
CHAPTER TWO.

36:12.738 --> 36:13.939
I READ IT.

36:13.939 --> 36:17.142
THAT STUFF IS REALLY
COMING OUT
THE WRONG END.

36:17.142 --> 36:18.610
SORRY YOU DIDN'T LIKE IT.

36:18.610 --> 36:20.812
THIS ISN'T JUST
SOME TERM PAPER.

36:20.812 --> 36:22.481
THIS IS MY LIFE.

36:22.481 --> 36:25.016
YOUR LIFE IS
A BUNCH OF PAPERS?

36:25.016 --> 36:28.754
MY DREAM IS TO GET
INTO GOVERNMENT
AND HELP PEOPLE.

36:28.754 --> 36:32.358
YOU THINK THOSE IDEAS
ARE GOING
TO HELP PEOPLE?

36:32.358 --> 36:35.494
IT'S A BUNCH OF
PESSIMISTIC JUNK.

36:35.494 --> 36:37.696
THAT'S NOT GOING
TO HELP.

36:37.696 --> 36:39.097
THAT'S GIVING UP.

36:39.097 --> 36:40.499
THE BEST PROFESSOR HERE

36:40.499 --> 36:42.901
HAPPENS TO THINK
THAT THIS HAS PROMISE.

36:42.901 --> 36:46.572
HIS OPINION, NOT YOURS.
THAT'S MY LIFE.

36:47.373 --> 36:49.375
WAIT A MINUTE, HARVARD.

36:49.375 --> 36:51.977
LET ME SHOW YOU MY LIFE.

36:56.648 --> 36:59.451
THERE IT IS.
THAT'S MY LIFE.

36:59.451 --> 37:02.688
I GOT THIS ONE
ON A BEACH IN BALI.

37:02.688 --> 37:05.291
BEST NIGHT'S SLEEP
I EVER HAD.

37:05.291 --> 37:08.994
YOU REMEMBER
ONE NIGHT OF SLEEP?

37:08.994 --> 37:11.263
THE LAST GOOD ONE I HAD.

37:12.998 --> 37:14.700
WHAT'S THIS SHINY WHITE ONE?

37:14.700 --> 37:19.070
YEAH, THAT ONE.
WHAT'S THAT?

37:19.070 --> 37:20.071
A WOMAN.

37:20.071 --> 37:21.673
WHO WAS SHE?

37:21.673 --> 37:23.542
THE ONE.

37:24.510 --> 37:27.513
MY ONE TRUE LOVE.

37:27.513 --> 37:30.416
HOW ABOUT THAT?
YOU'RE A ROMANTIC.

37:30.416 --> 37:33.352
ALL QUITTERS
ARE ROMANTIC, HARVARD.

37:35.186 --> 37:36.522
YEP.

37:36.522 --> 37:39.558
EACH STONE TELLS A STORY
THAT I WANT TO REMEMBER.

37:39.558 --> 37:43.061
ALL I DO--PUT THEM
IN MY HANDS, RUB THEM,

37:43.061 --> 37:45.597
AND ABRACADABRA,
I'M BACK THERE.

37:48.033 --> 37:49.801
GIVE ME YOUR BOOKS.

37:59.545 --> 38:01.747
TELL ME ABOUT THE WOMAN.

38:01.747 --> 38:02.748
I CAN'T.

38:02.748 --> 38:03.615
WHY NOT?

38:03.615 --> 38:05.984
I'M NOT HOLDING
THE STONE.

38:09.321 --> 38:12.524
WHY DON'T WE SIT DOWN?
THERE'S A BENCH.

38:16.194 --> 38:18.196
I ACTUALLY COME HERE
SOMETIMES

38:18.196 --> 38:19.931
WHEN THE WEATHER'S WARM.

38:19.931 --> 38:20.732
YEAH.

38:20.732 --> 38:22.133
IT'S BEAUTIFUL,
ISN'T IT?

38:22.133 --> 38:25.937
I GOT A FRIEND,
SLEEPS ON THAT BENCH
OVER THERE.

38:25.937 --> 38:27.939
I LIKE TO STUDY OUTSIDE.

38:27.939 --> 38:29.741
STUDY? BOY, OH, BOY,

38:29.741 --> 38:31.743
WHATEVER HAPPENED
TO YOU, ANYWAY,
HARVARD?

38:31.743 --> 38:34.746
DIDN'T YOUR FATHER
EVER PLAY BALL
WITH YOU?

38:34.746 --> 38:37.148
LET'S GO,
IF WE WANT TO GET
SOMETHING TO EAT.

38:37.148 --> 38:38.550
HEY, HEY, HEY.

38:38.550 --> 38:40.185
RELAX.
TAKE A BREATHER.

38:40.185 --> 38:41.720
YOU DIDN'T ANSWER
MY QUESTION.

38:41.720 --> 38:43.822
DIDN'T HE EVER
PLAY WITH YOU?

38:43.822 --> 38:46.758
MY PAST ISN'T PART
OF OUR DEAL.

38:46.758 --> 38:48.193
OOH.

38:48.193 --> 38:49.861
EXCUSE ME.

38:53.832 --> 38:57.035
YOU STILL DON'T THINK
I'M HUMAN, DO YOU?

39:01.339 --> 39:03.442
THERE'S NOTHING
TO TELL, O.K.?

39:03.442 --> 39:05.844
MY FATHER LEFT
WHEN I WAS 5.

39:05.844 --> 39:08.447
HE LEFT MY MOTHER
FOR ANOTHER WOMAN.

39:08.447 --> 39:11.450
HE HAD KIDS WITH HER.
WROTE ME ONCE A YEAR.

39:11.450 --> 39:12.851
WHEN I GOT INTO HARVARD,

39:12.851 --> 39:14.853
HE WROTE AND SAID
HOW PROUD HE WAS

39:14.853 --> 39:17.155
AND SORRY
HE COULDN'T HELP
WITH TUITION.

39:17.155 --> 39:20.959
THAT WAS THE LAST
I HEARD FROM HIM
'CAUSE HE DIED.

39:22.994 --> 39:24.396
MY MOM'S TERRIFIC.

39:24.396 --> 39:27.699
UNCLE BILL TOOK ME
TO LITTLE LEAGUE. O.K.?

39:27.699 --> 39:29.501
O.K.

39:29.501 --> 39:31.102
DOESN'T SOUND
TOO TOUGH.

39:31.102 --> 39:32.103
WAS IT?

39:35.373 --> 39:36.575
NO.

39:38.243 --> 39:39.978
HOW ABOUT YOU?

39:39.978 --> 39:41.012
WHAT?

39:41.012 --> 39:44.249
HOW LONG WERE YOU
IN THE MERCHANT MARINE?

39:44.249 --> 39:47.118
UM...NONE OF YOUR
GODDAMN BUSINESS.

40:02.668 --> 40:04.870
SO WHERE WERE YOU
BEFORE HARVARD?

40:04.870 --> 40:05.804
PRINCETON.

40:05.804 --> 40:08.273
I WAS HANGING OUT
WITH AL EINSTEIN.

40:08.273 --> 40:09.675
I KIND OF INSPIRED HIM.

40:09.675 --> 40:11.677
HE GOT STUCK
ON SOME FORMULA.

40:11.677 --> 40:14.079
I TOLD HIM,
"YOU GOT A STEADY JOB,

40:14.079 --> 40:16.682
"YOUR WIFE LOVES YOU.
DON'T MAKE YOURSELF CRAZY.

40:16.682 --> 40:17.883
EVERYTHING'S RELATIVE."

40:48.313 --> 40:50.315
THERE YOU ARE,
MR. FUEL PUMP.

40:50.315 --> 40:51.917
GOOD AS NEW.

40:54.720 --> 40:57.856
JUST IN TIME.
BREAKFAST.

40:57.856 --> 41:00.458
THERE YOU GO, BOY.
ONE PAGE.

41:00.458 --> 41:02.060
WHAT IS THIS?

41:02.060 --> 41:02.861
OATMEAL.

41:02.861 --> 41:05.330
ROUGHAGE.
IT'S GOOD FOR YOU.

41:05.330 --> 41:07.198
GOOD FOR A HORSE.

41:07.198 --> 41:09.601
GIVE ME THAT
PAGE BACK. HERE.

41:09.601 --> 41:11.202
EAT UP, SIMON.

41:11.202 --> 41:14.072
GOT A BIG SURPRISE
FOR YOU.

41:14.072 --> 41:15.874
OUR FOUNDING FATHERS,

41:15.874 --> 41:18.744
OR TO BE
POLITICALLY CORRECT,

41:18.744 --> 41:22.347
OUR FOUNDING PARENTS,

41:22.347 --> 41:25.483
DESIGNED THE CONSTITUTION
TO PREVENT THE PRESIDENCY

41:25.483 --> 41:28.954
FROM BECOMING ANOTHER FORM
OF TYRANNY,

41:28.954 --> 41:32.357
AN ELECTED KING.

41:32.357 --> 41:35.393
WELL, DID THEY SUCCEED?

41:35.393 --> 41:36.995
I SMELL AN AMBUSH.

41:36.995 --> 41:38.129
MISS MOORE,

41:38.129 --> 41:39.731
YOU HAVE AN ANSWER.

41:42.768 --> 41:45.503
THE PRESIDENT IS NOT
AN ELECTED KING.

41:45.503 --> 41:46.938
INDEED.

41:46.938 --> 41:49.608
COULD THE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES,

41:49.608 --> 41:52.410
WITHOUT CONSULTING
THOSE HE GOVERNS,

41:52.410 --> 41:55.847
MORE OR LESS DESTROY
THE ENTIRE WORLD?

41:55.847 --> 41:58.316
WELL, I GUESS HE COULD.

41:58.316 --> 41:59.718
YOU GUESS HE COULD.

41:59.718 --> 42:01.720
COULD JULIUS CAESAR
HAVE DONE THAT?

42:01.720 --> 42:02.721
COULD NAPOLEON?

42:02.721 --> 42:05.724
COULD ADOLF HITLER?

42:05.724 --> 42:07.058
BUT THEY TRIED TO.

42:07.058 --> 42:09.527
AREN'T YOU MAKING
A FALSE ANALOGY?

42:09.527 --> 42:12.463
OH, THIS IS
MY LUCKY DAY.

42:12.463 --> 42:13.865
I ASK A QUESTION,

42:13.865 --> 42:16.935
AND I GET A QUESTION
IN RESPONSE.

42:16.935 --> 42:20.138
YOU DO BELONG IN
GOVERNMENT, MY DEAR.

42:20.138 --> 42:21.539
SIT DOWN, PLEASE.

42:21.539 --> 42:24.275
NOW DOES ANYONE HAVE
AN ANSWER FOR ME

42:24.275 --> 42:25.677
INSTEAD OF A QUIZ?

42:25.677 --> 42:27.278
DON'T BE A HERO, BOY.

42:27.278 --> 42:29.147
MR. KESSLER.

42:29.147 --> 42:30.148
YOUR THOUGHTS.

42:30.148 --> 42:33.151
THE PRESIDENT CAN'T BOMB
WITHOUT REASON.

42:33.151 --> 42:34.552
HE HAS A REASON.

42:34.552 --> 42:37.823
HE THINKS WE NEED
MORE PARKING SPACES.

42:37.823 --> 42:40.826
THE POINT IS,
CAN HE DESTROY
THE WORLD?

42:40.826 --> 42:42.560
NOT WITHOUT CONGRESS.

42:42.560 --> 42:45.563
MR. KESSLER,
AFTER FOUR YEARS
OF HARVARD,

42:45.563 --> 42:47.232
HAS IT ESCAPED
YOUR ATTENTION

42:47.232 --> 42:50.435
THAT THE PRESIDENT
CAN MAKE WAR FOR 90 DAYS

42:50.435 --> 42:51.970
WITHOUT CONSULTING
CONGRESS?

42:51.970 --> 42:53.739
UH...

42:53.739 --> 42:55.707
WELL, THA-THAT'S RIGHT.

42:55.707 --> 42:57.843
THANK YOU VERY MUCH,
MR. KESSLER.

42:57.843 --> 43:01.412
AT LEAST I'M GOING
TO PASS THIS COURSE.

43:01.412 --> 43:03.048
SIT DOWN, PLEASE.

43:04.315 --> 43:07.352
MY QUESTION STILL STANDS.

43:07.352 --> 43:08.720
WHAT IS

43:08.720 --> 43:10.856
THE PARTICULAR GENIUS
OF THE CONSTITUTION?

43:10.856 --> 43:12.423
NICE TRY,
GENERAL CUSTER.

43:12.423 --> 43:13.825
SHUT UP.

43:13.825 --> 43:16.928
WHAT QUALITY DISTINGUISHES
THE AMERICAN CONSTITUTION?

43:16.928 --> 43:19.665
I TOLD YOU NOT
TO STAND UP.

43:19.665 --> 43:21.532
YOU CAN'T TALK
IN HERE.

43:21.532 --> 43:22.567
YOU, SIR.

43:22.567 --> 43:23.568
YOU, SIR!

43:23.568 --> 43:24.569
WHO, ME?

43:24.569 --> 43:26.604
DO YOU HAVE
AN OPINION?

43:26.604 --> 43:27.639
NO.

43:27.639 --> 43:29.975
ARE YOU A STUDENT?

43:29.975 --> 43:31.309
NO.

43:31.309 --> 43:34.279
ARE YOU A GUEST?

43:34.279 --> 43:36.682
NO, I'M A BUM.

43:36.682 --> 43:38.383
THERE ARE NO BUMS.

43:38.383 --> 43:41.386
THERE ARE ONLY
THE FINANCIALLY
CHALLENGED.

43:41.386 --> 43:43.154
NO, I'M A BUM...

43:43.154 --> 43:44.089
[LAUGHTER]

43:44.089 --> 43:46.792
BUT BEAR IN MIND,
I'M A HARVARD BUM.

43:46.792 --> 43:48.794
YOU MUST BE
THE LOGICAL RESULT

43:48.794 --> 43:51.029
OF AN OPEN
ADMISSIONS POLICY.

43:52.163 --> 43:53.131
NO, SIR.

43:53.131 --> 43:55.834
MY PRESENCE HERE
IS THE LOGICAL RESULT

43:55.834 --> 43:57.803
OF THE SEARCH
FOR EDIBLE GARBAGE.

43:57.803 --> 43:59.570
YOU'RE HERE
FOR THE GARBAGE.

43:59.570 --> 44:00.672
THAT'S RIGHT.

44:00.672 --> 44:03.008
COLLEGES PRODUCE
A LOT OF GARBAGE,

44:03.008 --> 44:05.911
AND HARVARD PRODUCES
MORE THAN MOST.

44:08.179 --> 44:10.315
WHAT WIT.

44:10.315 --> 44:12.450
INSPIRED NO DOUBT BY...

44:12.450 --> 44:14.185
WILD TURKEY?

44:15.320 --> 44:17.122
YOU ASK FOR CHARITY,

44:17.122 --> 44:19.390
PLEADING THAT SOCIETY
HAS FAILED YOU

44:19.390 --> 44:20.692
AND YOU NEED HELP,

44:20.692 --> 44:22.160
BUT ACTUALLY,
YOU'RE QUITE CAPABLE,

44:22.160 --> 44:27.265
AND WHAT YOU REALLY WANT
IS ALCOHOLIC BLISS.

44:31.002 --> 44:33.138
I WOULD RATHER DRINK
RUBBING ALCOHOL

44:33.138 --> 44:35.741
THAN LISTEN TO YOU,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN.

44:35.741 --> 44:38.143
AND ACCORDING TO
THE 21st AMENDMENT,

44:38.143 --> 44:41.012
YOU CAN DRINK
ANYTHING YOU WANT.

44:42.748 --> 44:43.749
SIMON.

44:43.749 --> 44:46.417
WHICH DOOR
DO I LEAVE FROM?

44:46.417 --> 44:50.221
AT HARVARD, WE DON'T
END OUR SENTENCES
WITH PREPOSITIONS.

44:50.221 --> 44:51.757
WELL, IN THAT CASE,

44:51.757 --> 44:54.960
WHICH DOOR DO
I LEAVE FROM, ASSHOLE?

44:56.594 --> 44:59.865
WHAT DEMOCRATIC ELOQUENCE.

45:01.199 --> 45:03.401
YOU ASKED
THE QUESTION, SIR.

45:03.401 --> 45:04.803
LET ME ANSWER IT.

45:04.803 --> 45:06.772
THE GENIUS
OF THE CONSTITUTION

45:06.772 --> 45:08.774
IS IT CAN ALWAYS
BE CHANGED.

45:08.774 --> 45:11.076
THE GENIUS
OF THE CONSTITUTION

45:11.076 --> 45:12.878
IS IT MAKES
NO PERMANENT RULE

45:12.878 --> 45:17.682
OTHER THAN ITS FAITH
IN THE WISDOM OF PEOPLE
TO GOVERN THEMSELVES.

45:17.682 --> 45:20.085
FAITH IN THE WISDOM
OF THE PEOPLE

45:20.085 --> 45:24.689
IS EXACTLY WHAT MAKES
THE CONSTITUTION
INCOMPLETE AND CRUDE.

45:24.689 --> 45:26.057
CRUDE?

45:26.057 --> 45:26.992
NO, SIR.

45:26.992 --> 45:28.459
OUR FOUNDING PARENTS

45:28.459 --> 45:30.929
WERE POMPOUS,
MIDDLE-AGED
WHITE FARMERS,

45:30.929 --> 45:32.931
BUT THEY WERE
ALSO GREAT MEN

45:32.931 --> 45:34.532
BECAUSE THEY KNEW
ONE THING

45:34.532 --> 45:36.534
THAT ALL GREAT MEN
SHOULD KNOW--

45:36.534 --> 45:37.936
THAT THEY DIDN'T
KNOW EVERYTHING.

45:37.936 --> 45:39.938
THEY KNEW THEY WOULD
MAKE MISTAKES,

45:39.938 --> 45:42.340
BUT THEY LEFT A WAY
TO CORRECT THEM.

45:42.340 --> 45:44.943
THEY DIDN'T THINK OF
THEMSELVES AS LEADERS.

45:44.943 --> 45:47.578
THEY WANTED
A GOVERNMENT
OF CITIZENS,

45:47.578 --> 45:48.814
NOT ROYALTY.

45:48.814 --> 45:50.949
A GOVERNMENT
OF LISTENERS,

45:50.949 --> 45:52.083
NOT LECTURERS.

45:52.083 --> 45:53.885
A GOVERNMENT
THAT COULD CHANGE,

45:53.885 --> 45:55.686
NOT STAND STILL.

45:55.686 --> 45:58.356
THE PRESIDENT
ISN'T AN ELECTED KING

45:58.356 --> 46:01.392
NO MATTER HOW MANY BOMBS
HE CAN DROP,

46:01.392 --> 46:05.230
BECAUSE THE CRUDE
CONSTITUTION
DOESN'T TRUST HIM.

46:05.230 --> 46:07.966
HE'S A SERVANT
OF THE PEOPLE.

46:07.966 --> 46:11.469
HE'S A BUM,
O.K., MR. PITKANNAN?

46:11.469 --> 46:13.304
HE'S JUST A BUM,

46:13.304 --> 46:16.107
AND THE ONLY BLISS
THAT HE'S SEARCHING FOR

46:16.107 --> 46:19.510
IS FREEDOM AND JUSTICE.

46:35.526 --> 46:36.928
MR. KESSLER.

46:38.997 --> 46:40.798
I'M SORRY, SIR.

46:42.333 --> 46:43.468
[COUGHING]

46:46.872 --> 46:48.840
SIMON.

46:48.840 --> 46:50.608
HEY, SIMON,
ARE YOU O.K.?

46:50.608 --> 46:52.343
WHAT CAN I DO?

47:00.751 --> 47:02.220
I'M FINE.

47:04.990 --> 47:07.993
NOW THAT I'VE TAUGHT
AT HARVARD, BOY,

47:07.993 --> 47:10.261
IT'S ALL DOWNHILL
FROM HERE.

47:25.510 --> 47:27.578
COURT, DO YOU THINK DEBBY

47:27.578 --> 47:29.580
IS A SEDUCTIVE PINOT NOIR

47:29.580 --> 47:31.249
OR A NUTTY CABERNET?

47:31.249 --> 47:33.584
DEBBY? WHAT HAPPENED
WITH HELGA?

47:33.584 --> 47:34.986
OH, I LOVE 'EM BOTH.

47:34.986 --> 47:36.988
WHEN ARE YOU
GOING TO REALIZE

47:36.988 --> 47:39.390
WOMEN ARE MORE THAN JUST
FERMENTED GRAPE JUICE?

47:39.390 --> 47:42.393
WHEN WILL YOU REALIZE
MEN ARE MORE THAN MEAT?

47:42.393 --> 47:44.395
THE DAY I BECOME
A VEGETARIAN.

47:44.395 --> 47:46.998
IT'S SUPPOSED TO GO
BELOW 0 TONIGHT.

47:46.998 --> 47:49.000
CAN HE SLEEP
IN THE CELLAR?

47:49.000 --> 47:50.401
NO PROBLEM.
SURE.

47:50.401 --> 47:52.737
NO PROBLEM?
THERE'S A BIG PROBLEM.

47:52.737 --> 47:54.139
I'M SICK OF THIS.

47:54.139 --> 47:57.542
I'M SICK OF PAYING EXTRA
TO LIVE WITH A BUM

47:57.542 --> 48:00.145
WHILE I GET RAGGED
BECAUSE I WANT TO STUDY.

48:00.145 --> 48:02.747
BRING HIM INSIDE,
AND I'M LEAVING.

48:02.747 --> 48:04.582
THEN LEAVE.

48:04.582 --> 48:05.750
I'M SERIOUS.

48:05.750 --> 48:08.954
ARE YOU GOING
TO COVER MY RENT?

48:09.754 --> 48:12.157
MONTY, I'D LOVE
TO HELP YOU OUT,

48:12.157 --> 48:15.426
BUT I'M BROKE.
MY OLD MAN CUT ME OFF.

48:15.426 --> 48:19.330
NOT THAT I EVER WANT
TO SEE JEFF LEAVE.

48:19.330 --> 48:20.298
NO PROBLEM.

48:20.298 --> 48:22.733
JUST TAKE ONE PORTION,
O.K.? JUST ONE.

48:22.733 --> 48:23.734
YOU SHIT!

48:23.734 --> 48:25.470
HE'S A HUMAN BEING.

48:25.470 --> 48:26.871
DON'T GIVE ME THAT.

48:26.871 --> 48:28.273
YOU JUST WANT
YOUR THESIS.

48:28.273 --> 48:32.210
YOU CARE ABOUT HIM?
TAKE HIM TO A SHELTER.

48:48.259 --> 48:50.395
SIMON.

48:50.395 --> 48:51.796
HA HA HA HA.

48:51.796 --> 48:54.432
AW, JESUS CHRIST!

48:54.432 --> 48:55.433
[COUGHING]

48:55.433 --> 48:57.402
HEY, HEY, HEY.

48:57.402 --> 48:58.203
HERE.

48:58.203 --> 48:59.804
I'M JUST PRACTICING.

48:59.804 --> 49:01.539
IT'S NOT A FUNNY JOKE.

49:01.539 --> 49:04.742
WHO SAID IT WAS A JOKE?

49:04.742 --> 49:06.811
WHERE'S THE BLANKET
I GAVE YOU?

49:06.811 --> 49:08.946
I LOANED IT TO A FRIEND.

49:08.946 --> 49:10.215
IN THIS COLD?

49:10.215 --> 49:12.283
WHAT ARE FRIENDS FOR?

49:14.085 --> 49:16.254
I'LL GET YOU
ANOTHER ONE.

49:16.254 --> 49:18.856
I WISH THIS THING'S
HEATER WORKED.

49:18.856 --> 49:20.858
HA HA HA. ME, TOO.

49:20.858 --> 49:24.129
THEN MY LIFE
WOULD BE PERFECT.

49:26.297 --> 49:27.298
WELL.

49:28.566 --> 49:29.967
HEY.

49:29.967 --> 49:32.037
I'LL DOUBLE
MY NORMAL PAYMENT

49:32.037 --> 49:35.173
FOR A LITTLE SPOT
IN THE CELLAR.

49:35.173 --> 49:37.708
UM, THE CELLAR'S
FLOODED,

49:37.708 --> 49:38.843
AND, UM--

49:38.843 --> 49:41.512
I WOULD PUT YOU
IN THE LIVING ROOM,

49:41.512 --> 49:44.449
BUT JEFF'S PARENTS MIGHT
BE COMING OVER TONIGHT,

49:44.449 --> 49:45.983
SO, YOU KNOW...

49:45.983 --> 49:49.054
WELL, SURE, I KNOW.

50:01.999 --> 50:03.334
I KNOW.

50:27.892 --> 50:29.494
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

50:31.028 --> 50:33.898
I'M THINKING,
WHY AM I IN HERE,

50:33.898 --> 50:35.500
AND HE'S OUT THERE?

50:44.709 --> 50:47.712
I DON'T THINK I'VE EVER
SEEN YOU LIKE THIS.

50:47.712 --> 50:51.516
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU'RE ABOUT
TO BURST INTO TEARS.

50:53.284 --> 50:55.486
WELL, DON'T HOLD
YOUR BREATH.

51:45.970 --> 51:47.372
SIMON?

51:51.842 --> 51:53.110
GOD.

51:53.110 --> 51:54.379
SIMON!

52:00.985 --> 52:02.587
"YOU LIED AGAIN, HARVARD.

52:02.587 --> 52:03.721
DEAL'S OFF."

52:09.894 --> 52:11.729
AAH!

52:30.748 --> 52:32.783
STOP!

52:32.783 --> 52:33.684
SHIT!

52:33.684 --> 52:36.621
SEPARATION ANXIETY
FROM YOUR CAST?

52:36.621 --> 52:39.224
I THOUGHT IT'D GO
QUICKER WITH IT OFF,

52:39.224 --> 52:41.626
BUT I CAN'T CONCENTRATE.
I CAN'T EVEN READ.

52:41.626 --> 52:45.029
I'M NEVER GOING
TO GET THIS DONE.

52:45.029 --> 52:46.931
THAT'S NOT YOUR PROBLEM.

52:46.931 --> 52:50.801
REALLY?
WHAT IS MY PROBLEM?

52:50.801 --> 52:53.037
YOU MISS HIM.

52:53.037 --> 52:55.373
DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

53:08.719 --> 53:10.187
GORKY.

53:10.187 --> 53:11.289
EVERETT!

53:11.289 --> 53:12.623
GORKY, COME--

53:15.159 --> 53:16.361
STUPID BIRD!

53:18.062 --> 53:19.797
GORKY! SHIT.

53:20.865 --> 53:22.533
[GLASS SHATTERS]

53:22.533 --> 53:24.101
EVERETT!

53:24.101 --> 53:26.337
GOOD MORNING.
ARE YOU AWAKE?

53:26.337 --> 53:28.172
EVERETT, COME GET
YOUR ROOSTER!

53:28.172 --> 53:29.307
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

53:29.307 --> 53:31.075
ALL RIGHT, NO PEEKING.

53:31.075 --> 53:33.544
NOPE, NO PEEKING.

53:34.745 --> 53:35.913
COURTNEY?

53:35.913 --> 53:38.082
MM-HMM.

53:38.082 --> 53:40.084
ALL RIGHT,
OPEN YOUR EYES.

53:40.084 --> 53:41.819
TA-DA.

53:43.754 --> 53:45.390
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

53:50.227 --> 53:51.228
THANK YOU.

53:51.228 --> 53:52.330
YOU'RE WELCOME.

53:52.330 --> 53:54.365
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

53:54.365 --> 53:56.867
YOU FALL, BOO-BOO?
DID YOU--

53:56.867 --> 53:57.868
GOOD MORNING.

53:57.868 --> 53:58.903
GOOD MORNING.

53:58.903 --> 54:02.239
GORKY, YOU TAKE GOOD CARE
OF LORD MONTAGUE

54:02.239 --> 54:04.709
WHILE WE'RE AWAY
ON CHRISTMAS BREAK.

54:04.709 --> 54:05.510
YOU SLEEPY?

54:05.510 --> 54:08.145
LET'S JUST TUCK YOU
IN HERE.

54:08.145 --> 54:10.114
NOW GIVE ME
A KISS GOODBYE.

54:10.114 --> 54:11.115
[SQUAWKS]

54:11.115 --> 54:12.317
OW! SHIT!

54:13.884 --> 54:15.520
OH, MY GOD.

54:15.520 --> 54:17.988
I REALLY HATE
THIS ROOSTER.

54:17.988 --> 54:18.923
[MONTY]
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

54:18.923 --> 54:21.191
MERRY CHRISTMAS.
CHRIST!

54:21.191 --> 54:22.993
SO HOW'S THE ANKLE?

54:22.993 --> 54:23.994
GOOD.

54:23.994 --> 54:25.796
SO YOU'LL BE
RACING ME SOON?

54:25.796 --> 54:29.400
I DON'T THINK I'LL EVER
REALLY CATCH UP TO YOU.

54:29.400 --> 54:32.570
COURT, LET'S GO.
BYE, MONTY.

54:33.838 --> 54:35.039
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

54:35.039 --> 54:36.474
HAPPY NEW YEAR.

54:36.474 --> 54:38.275
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

54:40.611 --> 54:44.482
SO WHY DON'T YOU
COME HOME WITH ME?

54:44.482 --> 54:46.351
SEE THE BIG APPLE,

54:46.351 --> 54:49.354
LET MY FOUR BROTHERS
BEAT YOU UP.

54:49.354 --> 54:51.956
I DON'T THINK
I'D BE GOOD COMPANY.

54:51.956 --> 54:53.358
WELL, I KNOW THAT.

54:53.358 --> 54:55.760
THE MAID'S OFF
FOR THE HOLIDAYS.

54:55.760 --> 54:59.364
WE COULD USE SOMEONE TO DO
A LITTLE LIGHT CLEANING.

54:59.364 --> 55:01.366
NOTHING BIG.
FLOOR-TO-CEILING WINDOWS

55:01.366 --> 55:03.368
THAT SHOULD SPARKLE
FOR THE HOLIDAYS.

55:03.368 --> 55:06.236
HEY, WHAT ABOUT
YOUR BOYFRIEND?

55:06.236 --> 55:09.840
ISN'T, UH, ISN'T
THREE A CROWD?

55:09.840 --> 55:11.576
THE FACE?

55:12.643 --> 55:16.381
HE WON'T BE THERE.
I DON'T BRING SEX HOME.

55:16.381 --> 55:17.982
RIGHT. I FORGOT.

55:19.717 --> 55:22.920
LISTEN, I'D LOVE TO MAKE
YOUR WINDOWS SPARKLE...

55:24.389 --> 55:26.591
BUT I GOT TO WORK.

55:29.460 --> 55:31.328
[JEFF]
COURTNEY, COME ON!

55:34.031 --> 55:37.835
IF ANYTHING CHANGES,
JUST GIVE ME A CALL, O.K.?

55:47.878 --> 55:49.414
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

56:06.163 --> 56:08.132
HI, MOM. IT'S ME.

56:08.132 --> 56:09.834
FINE.

56:09.834 --> 56:12.537
I KNOW. I'M REALLY
DISAPPOINTED, TOO.

56:12.537 --> 56:15.740
I JUST--I'VE GOT
TOO MUCH WORK TO DO.

56:15.740 --> 56:16.841
I--

56:18.543 --> 56:20.210
IT'S TOO EXPENSIVE.

56:20.210 --> 56:22.112
NO. MOM--

56:22.112 --> 56:25.015
I'LL CALL YOU
ON CHRISTMAS MORNING, O.K.?

56:25.015 --> 56:27.117
ALL RIGHT?

56:27.117 --> 56:29.319
O.K.

56:29.319 --> 56:30.455
O.K.

56:30.455 --> 56:32.056
I LOVE YOU.

56:34.124 --> 56:35.125
BYE.

56:43.734 --> 56:45.936
DO YOU LOVE ME, GORKY?

56:50.040 --> 56:51.208
GORKY...

56:52.042 --> 56:54.845
ARE YOU AND EVERETT
SLEEPING TOGETHER?

56:56.514 --> 56:59.383
I THOUGHT SO.

56:59.383 --> 57:01.819
I'M TALKING TO A CHICKEN.

57:01.819 --> 57:03.220
[SQUAWKS]

57:03.220 --> 57:05.389
AAH!

57:05.389 --> 57:10.695
* JACK FROST
NIPPING AT YOUR NOSE *

57:12.262 --> 57:14.799
* YULETIDE CAROLS *

57:14.799 --> 57:18.569
* BEING SUNG BY A CHOIR *

57:18.569 --> 57:24.374
* AND FOLKS DRESSED UP
LIKE ESKIMOS *

57:24.374 --> 57:27.377
* EVERYBODY KNOWS *

57:27.377 --> 57:32.282
* A TURKEY
AND SOME MISTLETOE *

57:33.217 --> 57:38.689
* HELP TO MAKE
THE SEASON BRIGHT *

57:40.390 --> 57:42.392
* TINY TOTS *

57:42.392 --> 57:45.796
* WITH THEIR EYES
ALL AGLOW *

57:45.796 --> 57:49.033
* WILL FIND IT
HARD TO SLEEP *

57:49.033 --> 57:52.737
* TONIGHT **

57:54.539 --> 57:56.140
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

58:06.150 --> 58:07.151
SIMON.

58:08.619 --> 58:10.220
ARE YOU HARVARD?

58:10.220 --> 58:12.289
UM...THAT'S
MY BLANKET.

58:12.289 --> 58:13.457
IT'S SIMON'S.

58:13.457 --> 58:16.561
HE GAVE IT TO ME
FOR KEEPING THIS SAFE.

58:16.561 --> 58:19.029
I'M TO GIVE THIS TO YOU
AND A MESSAGE.

58:19.029 --> 58:21.632
HE SAID YOU'D GIVE ME
SOMETHING TO EAT.

58:21.632 --> 58:24.301
HE SAID IT SHOULDN'T
BE ROUGHAGE.

58:24.301 --> 58:26.170
YEAH. COME ON IN.

58:26.170 --> 58:27.705
HA-HAVE A SEAT. I--

58:27.705 --> 58:29.907
I WAS HAVING
A SANDWICH.

58:29.907 --> 58:30.941
IS, UH...

58:32.176 --> 58:33.578
HAM AND CHEESE O.K.?

58:33.578 --> 58:35.580
YEAH,
W-WITH MUSTARD.

58:35.580 --> 58:37.181
SO WHAT'S THE MESSAGE?

58:37.181 --> 58:39.016
OH...DON'T YOU
WANT THIS?

58:39.016 --> 58:41.852
SIMON SAID YOU'D THINK
CHRIST DIED FOR THIS.

58:41.852 --> 58:45.055
JUST LEAVE IT
ON THE TABLE.

58:45.055 --> 58:46.056
SO, UH...

58:46.056 --> 58:47.858
WHAT'S HIS MESSAGE?

58:49.994 --> 58:52.797
NOW, I--I GOT
TO GET THIS RIGHT.

58:57.001 --> 59:00.104
NOW, THIS IS
SIMON WILDER'S MESSAGE.

59:01.739 --> 59:03.741
"YOU SHALL NO LONGER
TAKE THINGS

59:03.741 --> 59:05.843
"AT SECOND
OR THIRD HAND,

59:05.843 --> 59:08.245
"NOR LOOK THROUGH
THE EYES OF THE DEAD,

59:08.245 --> 59:10.848
"NOR FEED
ON THE SPECTERS
IN BOOKS.

59:10.848 --> 59:13.450
"YOU SHALL NOT LOOK
THROUGH MY EYES EITHER,

59:13.450 --> 59:15.452
"NOR TAKE THINGS
FROM ME.

59:15.452 --> 59:17.454
"YOU SHALL LISTEN
TO ALL SIDES

59:17.454 --> 59:19.924
AND FILTER THEM
FROM YOURSELF."

59:21.291 --> 59:22.960
THAT'S IT.

59:23.761 --> 59:25.462
I DID IT PERFECT.

59:25.462 --> 59:27.632
WHY DIDN'T HE
COME HIMSELF?

59:27.632 --> 59:29.499
IS HE O.K.?

59:29.499 --> 59:30.635
HE'S FINE.

59:30.635 --> 59:32.236
WHERE IS HE?

59:33.638 --> 59:35.973
HE DOESN'T WANT
TO SEE YOU.

59:38.375 --> 59:40.177
I DON'T WANT
TO BOTHER HIM,

59:40.177 --> 59:43.180
BUT I WANT TO
MAKE SURE HE HAS
SOMEPLACE TO STAY.

59:43.180 --> 59:45.315
AS LONG AS YOU UNDERSTAND
HE DOESN'T WANT TO SEE YOU,

59:45.315 --> 59:49.854
I'M SUPPOSED TO SAY
HE'S AT ST. PETER'S
CHURCH SHELTER.

59:50.655 --> 59:52.356
IS THAT
A GOOD SHELTER?

59:53.924 --> 59:56.593
WELL, YEAH.
IT'S JUST GREAT.

01:00:01.531 --> 01:00:03.267
WELL, GOOD.

01:00:03.267 --> 01:00:04.368
GOOD.

01:00:06.236 --> 01:00:07.838
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

01:00:09.139 --> 01:00:11.308
[KNOCK KNOCK]

01:00:12.542 --> 01:00:15.145
HELLO. UH, WHERE'S
THE MEN'S SHELTER?

01:00:15.145 --> 01:00:16.146
SHELTER? HERE?

01:00:16.146 --> 01:00:16.947
YEAH.

01:00:16.947 --> 01:00:18.548
THERE'S NO SHELTER
HERE.

01:00:18.548 --> 01:00:19.549
YOU SURE?

01:00:19.549 --> 01:00:21.285
WORKED HERE
FOR 32 YEARS.

01:00:21.285 --> 01:00:22.687
I OUGHT TO KNOW.

01:00:22.687 --> 01:00:25.089
CLOSEST THING
TO A SHELTER
AROUND HERE

01:00:25.089 --> 01:00:27.291
IS OVER THERE
IN THE ALLEY.

01:00:27.291 --> 01:00:28.625
THANK YOU.

01:00:47.712 --> 01:00:49.146
[COUGH COUGH]

01:00:54.584 --> 01:00:56.186
LEAVE THAT ALONE.

01:00:56.186 --> 01:00:57.321
[COUGHING]

01:00:57.321 --> 01:01:00.057
[COUGH COUGH]

01:01:00.057 --> 01:01:01.325
SIMON.

01:01:01.325 --> 01:01:02.326
SIMON.

01:01:02.326 --> 01:01:03.327
[COUGH COUGH]

01:01:03.327 --> 01:01:04.361
HEY.

01:01:04.361 --> 01:01:06.797
HEY, HEY, WHAT DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE DOING?

01:01:06.797 --> 01:01:08.799
I'M TAKING YOU
TO THE HOSPITAL.

01:01:08.799 --> 01:01:10.534
NO. NO HOSPITAL. UH-UH.

01:01:10.534 --> 01:01:11.535
YOU'RE SICK.

01:01:11.535 --> 01:01:12.536
NO HOSPITAL.

01:01:12.536 --> 01:01:13.537
LISTEN. LISTEN.

01:01:13.537 --> 01:01:15.539
YOU GOT TO
PROMISE ME...

01:01:15.539 --> 01:01:17.141
NO MATTER
WHAT HAPPENS...

01:01:18.142 --> 01:01:18.943
NO HOSPITAL.

01:01:18.943 --> 01:01:20.544
SIMON, YOU'RE SICK.

01:01:20.544 --> 01:01:22.747
NO LIES!

01:01:22.747 --> 01:01:23.748
[COUGH]

01:01:23.748 --> 01:01:24.749
JUST PROMISE.

01:01:24.749 --> 01:01:26.751
[COUGH COUGH]

01:01:26.751 --> 01:01:27.752
DAMN IT!

01:01:27.752 --> 01:01:29.954
[COUGH COUGH]

01:01:31.756 --> 01:01:33.357
O.K., I PROMISE.

01:01:33.357 --> 01:01:34.358
O.K.?

01:01:34.358 --> 01:01:35.359
ALL RIGHT.

01:01:35.359 --> 01:01:36.360
O.K.

01:01:40.765 --> 01:01:41.766
[COUGH COUGH]

01:01:41.766 --> 01:01:42.967
COME ON.

01:01:52.910 --> 01:01:54.711
HEY, YOU'RE AWAKE.

01:01:56.646 --> 01:01:57.848
BREAKFAST.

01:01:58.648 --> 01:02:00.050
HERE. EAT UP.

01:02:00.050 --> 01:02:02.853
YOU ARE SEEING
A DOCTOR THIS AFTERNOON.

01:02:03.788 --> 01:02:05.455
IS THIS YOUR ROOM,
HARVARD?

01:02:05.455 --> 01:02:07.324
NO, THIS IS BOZ' ROOM.

01:02:07.324 --> 01:02:08.325
BUT, UM...

01:02:09.693 --> 01:02:11.295
IT'S YOUR ROOM NOW.

01:02:11.295 --> 01:02:12.296
HERE.

01:02:14.464 --> 01:02:16.066
WHAT'S THIS FOR?

01:02:17.134 --> 01:02:18.068
THE DOOR.

01:02:18.068 --> 01:02:21.138
YOU CAN COME AND GO
AS YOU PLEASE.

01:02:21.138 --> 01:02:24.741
NO WILD PARTIES.
I GOT WORK TO DO.

01:02:24.741 --> 01:02:26.176
MY LUNGS, HARVARD.

01:02:26.176 --> 01:02:28.712
I'LL BE O.K.
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS.

01:02:28.712 --> 01:02:30.547
IS IT SMOKING? IS...

01:02:30.547 --> 01:02:32.349
ISN'T THAT
WHAT HAPPENED?

01:02:32.349 --> 01:02:34.418
SMOKING, NO.

01:02:34.418 --> 01:02:36.353
ASBESTOS.

01:02:36.353 --> 01:02:38.956
IT WAS
IN THE SHIPYARDS
IN BALTIMORE.

01:02:38.956 --> 01:02:41.458
IT WAS ON
THE MERCHANT SHIP,
TOO.

01:02:41.458 --> 01:02:44.061
WE BREATHED IT WHEN
WE WERE BUILDING THEM,

01:02:44.061 --> 01:02:46.997
AND WE BREATHED IT
WHEN WE SAILED THEM,

01:02:46.997 --> 01:02:48.398
AND THEY KNEW IT.

01:02:48.398 --> 01:02:51.335
THEY ALSO KNEW
THAT IT WOULD
TAKE 20 YEARS

01:02:51.335 --> 01:02:52.837
TO KILL YOU.

01:02:55.840 --> 01:02:58.308
MMM. AND THAT'S
WHY YOU QUIT.

01:02:59.709 --> 01:03:01.045
MY LUNGS QUIT.

01:03:01.045 --> 01:03:02.779
I DIDN'T QUIT.

01:03:03.981 --> 01:03:07.184
I COULDN'T WORK.
THEY FIRED ME.

01:03:12.589 --> 01:03:15.025
WELL, TRY AND GET
SOME REST.

01:03:15.993 --> 01:03:17.794
HEY, WAIT A SECOND.

01:03:19.029 --> 01:03:21.832
GOT YOUR THESIS BACK,
SO WHAT'S OUR DEAL?

01:03:21.832 --> 01:03:23.834
WE DON'T NEED A DEAL.

01:03:23.834 --> 01:03:26.703
WE HAVE TO HAVE
A DEAL, HARVARD.

01:03:26.703 --> 01:03:29.706
I GOT TO PAY
MY OWN WAY.

01:03:29.706 --> 01:03:32.176
HOW YOU GONNA
MANAGE THAT?

01:03:32.176 --> 01:03:37.147
DON'T YOU KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT GOVERNMENT
AT ALL, BOY?

01:03:37.147 --> 01:03:40.584
I'M ENTITLED
TO DISABILITY BENEFITS.

01:03:43.888 --> 01:03:46.891
I THINK
IT'S ABOUT TIME
I KISSED AND MADE UP

01:03:46.891 --> 01:03:49.226
WITH MY GOOD OLD
UNCLE SAMMY.

01:03:55.365 --> 01:03:56.600
THANKS, HARVARD.

01:04:05.009 --> 01:04:08.078
I ASSUME
YOUR FATHER TOLD YOU
ABOUT HIS CONDITION.

01:04:08.078 --> 01:04:09.679
HE'S NOT MY FATHER.

01:04:09.679 --> 01:04:11.081
HE'S A FRIEND.

01:04:11.081 --> 01:04:13.683
HE SAYS ASBESTOS
DID IT TO HIM.

01:04:13.683 --> 01:04:14.684
ASBESTOSIS.

01:04:14.684 --> 01:04:16.486
THAT'S RIGHT.

01:04:16.486 --> 01:04:19.689
MR. WILDER WAS EXPOSED
MANY YEARS AGO.

01:04:19.689 --> 01:04:22.092
THE LUNGS CAN'T EXPEL
THE FIBERS,

01:04:22.092 --> 01:04:24.528
AND HE'S IN
THE FINAL STAGES.

01:04:24.528 --> 01:04:27.464
YOU MEAN HE--
ISN'T IT TREATABLE...
AT ALL?

01:04:27.464 --> 01:04:30.034
THERE'S NO TREATMENT
AT ANY STAGE.

01:04:30.034 --> 01:04:32.869
BASICALLY, THE LUNGS
CAN'T TAKE IN AIR.

01:04:32.869 --> 01:04:34.671
OFTEN THE PATIENT
SUCCUMBS TO PNEUMONIA,

01:04:34.671 --> 01:04:38.275
OR THE STRAIN
ON THE HEART CAUSES
CARDIAC ARREST.

01:04:38.275 --> 01:04:41.011
THERE'S REALLY
NOTHING TO DO
BUT WAIT.

01:04:41.011 --> 01:04:43.280
I'M SORRY.

01:05:51.615 --> 01:05:55.152
[SIMON]
HARVARD! DINNER'S SERVED!
GET IT DOWN HERE, BOY!

01:06:07.831 --> 01:06:08.832
WELL.

01:06:08.832 --> 01:06:10.234
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

01:06:10.234 --> 01:06:12.636
WHAT? IT'S A MIRACLE
I CAN COOK?

01:06:12.636 --> 01:06:16.506
EASY. YOU JUST TALK
A LITTLE FRENCHY
WHILE YOU'RE DOING IT.

01:06:16.506 --> 01:06:19.643
I COULD USE A GOOD MEAL
BEFORE GETTING BACK
TO WORK.

01:06:19.643 --> 01:06:23.780
WORK? IT'S NEW YEAR'S EVE.
WHO DO YOU THINK
YOU ARE, DICK CLARK?

01:06:23.780 --> 01:06:25.915
BESIDES, I GAVE YOU
YOUR THESIS.

01:06:25.915 --> 01:06:28.318
YOU SHOULD BE FINISHED
BY NOW.

01:06:28.318 --> 01:06:29.919
OH, I'M STARTING OVER.

01:06:29.919 --> 01:06:32.122
YOU TOSSED IT?
THE WHOLE THING?

01:06:32.122 --> 01:06:33.123
YEAH. GONE.

01:06:33.123 --> 01:06:34.991
BOY, OH, BOY.
EAT UP.

01:06:34.991 --> 01:06:37.261
WANT TO HEAR WHAT
THE NEW ONE'S ON?

01:06:37.261 --> 01:06:39.863
NOPE. BEHOLD,
I DO NOT GIVE LECTURES

01:06:39.863 --> 01:06:41.265
OR A LITTLE CHARITY.

01:06:41.265 --> 01:06:44.468
WHEN I GIVE...
I GIVE MYSELF.

01:06:44.468 --> 01:06:45.869
THIS IS GREAT.

01:06:45.869 --> 01:06:48.272
YOU MUST
BE FEELING BETTER.

01:06:48.272 --> 01:06:50.874
YOU WENT OUT
AND SHOPPED.

01:06:50.874 --> 01:06:52.609
I DIDN'T GO OUT.

01:06:52.609 --> 01:06:54.010
I EAT WHAT'S HANDY.

01:06:54.010 --> 01:06:55.279
WASN'T HARD...

01:06:55.279 --> 01:06:57.781
EXCEPT FOR THE PLUCKING.

01:06:57.781 --> 01:06:59.015
PLUCKING?

01:06:59.015 --> 01:07:00.750
MMM.

01:07:05.889 --> 01:07:08.092
GORKY?

01:07:09.025 --> 01:07:10.627
GORKY!

01:07:10.627 --> 01:07:11.895
GORKY?

01:07:11.895 --> 01:07:14.231
HAPPY NEW YEAR,
HARVARD.

01:07:26.510 --> 01:07:28.212
HOLY SHIT!

01:07:28.212 --> 01:07:29.713
YOU THINK SO?

01:07:29.713 --> 01:07:32.048
LOOKS LIKE THE REGULAR
GARDEN VARIETY TO ME.

01:07:32.048 --> 01:07:33.517
UH...

01:07:33.517 --> 01:07:34.418
MONTY!

01:07:34.418 --> 01:07:37.754
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
SHUT THE DOOR.

01:07:37.754 --> 01:07:38.655
BIG BABY.

01:07:38.655 --> 01:07:41.091
NOW HE'LL PROBABLY
TELL EVERYBODY.

01:07:41.091 --> 01:07:42.926
MONTY, HE IS
IN THE BATHROOM.

01:07:42.926 --> 01:07:44.328
HI. WHEN'D
YOU GET BACK?

01:07:44.328 --> 01:07:46.930
WHAT THE HELL
IS HE DOING IN THERE?

01:07:46.930 --> 01:07:48.332
TAKING A DUMP?

01:07:48.332 --> 01:07:51.501
THAT BOY DIDN'T GO
TO HARVARD FOR NOTHING.

01:07:51.501 --> 01:07:53.103
[COURTNEY]
HONEY, I'M HOME!

01:07:53.103 --> 01:07:54.671
HE GOES RIGHT NOW.

01:07:57.174 --> 01:07:58.608
PEACE, CHILDREN.

01:07:58.608 --> 01:08:01.611
MR. WILDER,
HOW NICE TO SEE YOU.

01:08:01.611 --> 01:08:04.948
I'M SORRY, JEFF,
BUT HE'S OUR NEW BOZ.

01:08:04.948 --> 01:08:06.350
YEAH, THAT'S ME. BOZ.

01:08:06.350 --> 01:08:08.152
I JUST FLEW IN
FROM BALI.

01:08:08.152 --> 01:08:11.054
BOZ,
MY LONG-LOST BROTHER.

01:08:11.054 --> 01:08:12.456
WHERE'S YOUR TAN,
MAN?

01:08:12.456 --> 01:08:13.757
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

01:08:13.757 --> 01:08:16.359
HE'S GOT MONEY COMING IN
FROM SOCIAL SECURITY.

01:08:16.359 --> 01:08:19.828
HE CAN PAY FOR RENT
AND EVEN KICK IN
FOR FOOD.

01:08:19.828 --> 01:08:22.566
I HAVE THE FULL BACKING
OF THE UNITED STATES
GOVERNMENT.

01:08:22.566 --> 01:08:24.100
COURTNEY.

01:08:24.100 --> 01:08:27.837
* GOD LOVES AMERICANS *

01:08:27.837 --> 01:08:30.240
* AND ALSO MEXICANS *

01:08:30.240 --> 01:08:31.975
* AND RUSSIANS-- **

01:08:31.975 --> 01:08:33.777
WILL YOU STOP SINGING?

01:08:33.777 --> 01:08:35.879
SING A SONG EVERYDAY.
KEEP YOUR VOICES
HIGH AND GAY.

01:08:35.879 --> 01:08:36.912
IF EVERYBODY
SINGS A SONG,

01:08:36.912 --> 01:08:38.381
NEVER WILL
THE WORLD GO WRONG.

01:08:38.381 --> 01:08:41.651
SO HE CAN'T CARRY A TUNE,
BUT CAN HE COOK?

01:08:41.651 --> 01:08:44.453
DOES MADONNA
TAKE HER CLOTHES OFF?

01:08:44.453 --> 01:08:45.421
EVERETT.

01:08:45.421 --> 01:08:47.857
DO SADDAM HUSSEIN
AND MUAMMAR KHADAFY

01:08:47.857 --> 01:08:49.259
PULL EACH OTHER'S
TOFFEE?

01:08:49.259 --> 01:08:50.926
YES! BUT I DON'T
DO WINDOWS.

01:08:50.926 --> 01:08:52.328
O.K., YOU GOT FRIDAYS.

01:08:52.328 --> 01:08:54.997
NO, NO. I WILL NOT
PUT UP WITH THIS.

01:08:54.997 --> 01:08:56.064
THEN DON'T.

01:08:56.064 --> 01:08:58.001
MR. WILDER
WILL COVER YOUR RENT.

01:08:58.001 --> 01:09:00.002
GET OUT OF MY WAY, JEFF.

01:09:00.002 --> 01:09:01.305
SHE'S RIGHT, BOY,

01:09:01.305 --> 01:09:02.906
YOU BIG BABY.

01:09:02.906 --> 01:09:04.408
I HAVE A COMPLAINT.

01:09:04.408 --> 01:09:07.310
BOY, OH, BOY.
LET ME HELP YOU
WITH THIS.

01:09:07.310 --> 01:09:09.513
MY VAN STILL
ISN'T FIXED.

01:09:11.113 --> 01:09:14.318
THAT'S BECAUSE
I RAN OUT OF WINE.

01:09:16.085 --> 01:09:17.487
[JEFF]
OH, MY GOD!

01:09:17.487 --> 01:09:19.256
HE DIDN'T EVEN FLUSH!

01:09:19.256 --> 01:09:21.725
[TOILET FLUSHING]

01:09:43.412 --> 01:09:45.881
* BLUE SKIES *

01:09:45.881 --> 01:09:48.618
* SMILIN' AT ME *

01:09:48.618 --> 01:09:51.755
* NOTHIN' BUT BLUE SKIES *

01:09:51.755 --> 01:09:54.189
* DO I SEE *

01:09:55.158 --> 01:09:57.561
* BLUE DAYS *

01:09:57.561 --> 01:10:00.430
* ALL OF THEM GONE *

01:10:00.430 --> 01:10:03.767
* NOTHIN' BUT BLUE SKIES *

01:10:03.767 --> 01:10:07.871
* FROM NOW ON *

01:10:07.871 --> 01:10:08.905
* NEVER SAW THE SUN *

01:10:08.905 --> 01:10:10.374
* SHININ' SO BRIGHT *

01:10:10.374 --> 01:10:11.975
* NEVER SAW THINGS *

01:10:11.975 --> 01:10:13.377
* GOIN' SO RIGHT *

01:10:13.377 --> 01:10:15.044
* NOTICIN' THE DAYS *

01:10:15.044 --> 01:10:16.346
* HURRYIN' BY *

01:10:16.346 --> 01:10:17.947
* WHEN YOU'RE IN LOVE *

01:10:17.947 --> 01:10:19.849
* MY, HOW THEY FLY BY *

01:10:19.849 --> 01:10:21.851
* BLUE DAYS *

01:10:21.851 --> 01:10:24.721
* ALL OF THEM GONE *

01:10:24.721 --> 01:10:27.591
* NOTHIN' BUT BLUE SKIES *

01:10:27.591 --> 01:10:28.592
* FROM NOW ON... *

01:10:28.592 --> 01:10:30.159
IT'S THE IDES OF MARCH.

01:10:30.159 --> 01:10:32.562
TO CELEBRATE,
WE HAVE A GUEST.

01:10:32.562 --> 01:10:34.163
IS IT WHITMAN'S GHOST?

01:10:34.163 --> 01:10:37.166
IS IT THE SLAYER
OF DRAGON PITKANNAN?

01:10:37.166 --> 01:10:38.802
NO, IT'S...

01:10:38.802 --> 01:10:41.137
THE BUM OF THE MONTH.

01:10:41.137 --> 01:10:42.606
YOU'RE A WIDELY
TRAVELED MAN.

01:10:42.606 --> 01:10:44.007
IN FACT,
YOU'RE AN EXPERT

01:10:44.007 --> 01:10:46.310
ON LIVING COMFORTABLY
AWAY FROM HOME.

01:10:46.310 --> 01:10:49.813
WOULD YOU SAY HARVARD
IS YOUR FAVORITE SPOT?

01:10:49.813 --> 01:10:50.814
NO WAY...

01:10:50.814 --> 01:10:51.815
JOSE.

01:10:51.815 --> 01:10:53.216
NO?

01:10:53.216 --> 01:10:55.819
WELL, WHAT'S
YOUR FAVORITE SPOT?

01:10:55.819 --> 01:10:58.221
MY FAVORITE PLACE...

01:10:58.221 --> 01:11:00.824
IS A LEPER COLONY
IN MOLOKAI.

01:11:00.824 --> 01:11:02.225
A LEPER COLONY?

01:11:02.225 --> 01:11:03.226
IN MOLOKAI.

01:11:03.226 --> 01:11:04.628
WHY?

01:11:04.628 --> 01:11:08.498
BECAUSE I WAS THE MOST
HANDSOME GUY THERE.

01:11:08.498 --> 01:11:11.234
HEY, JEFF,
MAYBE MOLOKAI'S
WHERE YOU SHOULD GO.

01:11:11.234 --> 01:11:12.569
[SNICKERS]

01:11:20.109 --> 01:11:21.545
* BLUE SKIES *

01:11:21.545 --> 01:11:24.714
* SMILIN' AT ME *

01:11:24.714 --> 01:11:27.917
* NOTHIN' BUT BLUE SKIES *

01:11:27.917 --> 01:11:30.420
* DO I SEE *

01:11:31.388 --> 01:11:33.657
* BLUE DAYS *

01:11:33.657 --> 01:11:36.726
* ALL OF THEM GONE *

01:11:36.726 --> 01:11:39.529
* NOTHIN' BUT BLUE SKIES *

01:11:39.529 --> 01:11:40.930
* FROM NOW ON... **

01:11:40.930 --> 01:11:43.667
IS THAT FRENCH TOAST?
I LOVE FRENCH TOAST.

01:11:43.667 --> 01:11:45.869
EVEN IF IT'S MADE
BY MY HANDS?

01:11:45.869 --> 01:11:47.504
YOU STILL INTERESTED?

01:11:49.873 --> 01:11:51.675
AHH. DONE JUST RIGHT.

01:11:51.675 --> 01:11:54.277
YOU PUT YOUR SOCKS
IN THE OVEN?

01:11:54.277 --> 01:11:56.680
SURE. 250 DEGREES
FOR 5 MINUTES.

01:11:56.680 --> 01:11:58.682
I LIKE MY TOES
TOASTY WARM.

01:11:58.682 --> 01:12:01.351
YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT SOME?

01:12:01.351 --> 01:12:02.686
NOT NOW.

01:12:02.686 --> 01:12:04.087
LITTLE SQUEAMISH
FOR SOMEBODY

01:12:04.087 --> 01:12:06.890
WHO'S GOING TO
BECOME A DOCTOR,
AIN'T YA?

01:12:06.890 --> 01:12:08.291
I'M NOT SQUEAMISH.

01:12:08.291 --> 01:12:10.026
NO?

01:12:10.026 --> 01:12:12.896
WHAT KIND OF DOCTOR
ARE YOU GOING TO BE?

01:12:12.896 --> 01:12:13.897
GYNECOLOGIST.

01:12:13.897 --> 01:12:14.898
THAT'S GOOD.

01:12:14.898 --> 01:12:16.833
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
YOU'LL EVER GET

01:12:16.833 --> 01:12:18.502
SOME YOUNG SWEET THING
TO DROP HER DRAWERS.

01:12:18.502 --> 01:12:20.904
ARE YOU THE CASANOVA
OF SKID ROW?

01:12:20.904 --> 01:12:22.305
HEH HEH HEH HEH.

01:12:22.305 --> 01:12:24.541
YOU KNOW WHY
YOU HATE ME SO MUCH?

01:12:24.541 --> 01:12:27.343
I LOOK
THE WAY YOU FEEL.

01:12:45.962 --> 01:12:49.298
SO WHY DO YOU THINK
THE KIDS TEASE YOU?

01:12:49.298 --> 01:12:51.535
THEY'RE JEALOUS
'CAUSE I'M SO HANDSOME.

01:13:04.681 --> 01:13:06.349
WELL?

01:13:06.349 --> 01:13:07.951
PITKANNAN'S
GOING TO IMPLODE.

01:13:07.951 --> 01:13:09.218
WHY?

01:13:09.218 --> 01:13:12.355
YOU'RE ATTACKING
HIS WHOLE BELIEF SYSTEM,
WEREN'T YOU?

01:13:12.355 --> 01:13:14.758
THIS HAS NONE
OF HIS PESSIMISM.

01:13:14.758 --> 01:13:16.760
"ADVANCES IN COMMUNICATION
AND TECHNOLOGY

01:13:16.760 --> 01:13:18.762
"WILL EVENTUALLY ALLOW
THE UNITED STATES

01:13:18.762 --> 01:13:21.364
TO ACCOMPLISH ITS DREAM
OF PURE DEMOCRACY."

01:13:21.364 --> 01:13:22.766
THAT'S RIGHT.

01:13:22.766 --> 01:13:25.368
INTERACTIVE CABLE'S
GOING TO SAVE THE WORLD.

01:13:25.368 --> 01:13:27.771
ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS PROVE IT.

01:13:27.771 --> 01:13:30.173
IT'S CRAZY. IT'S GREAT.
I LOVE IT.

01:13:30.173 --> 01:13:33.376
I DON'T KNOW HOW
I'LL GET THIS DONE
IN FOUR WEEKS.

01:13:33.376 --> 01:13:36.379
MAYBE PITKANNAN WILL
GIVE YOU AN EXTENSION.

01:13:36.379 --> 01:13:38.381
NO. IF I DON'T
HAVE IT IN ON TIME,

01:13:38.381 --> 01:13:40.216
I DON'T GRADUATE
WITH HONORS.

01:13:40.216 --> 01:13:42.351
YOU CAN DO IT.

01:13:42.351 --> 01:13:45.121
YOU HAVE CONFIDENCE
IN ME?

01:13:45.121 --> 01:13:47.123
YES.

01:13:47.123 --> 01:13:49.258
NO CRITICISM?

01:13:49.258 --> 01:13:52.128
WELL, MAYBE ONE.

01:13:53.396 --> 01:13:55.131
YOU'RE PERFECT.

01:14:00.003 --> 01:14:01.404
WELL--AHEM--

01:14:01.404 --> 01:14:04.641
I BETTER LET YOU
GET BACK TO WORK.

01:14:04.641 --> 01:14:08.011
WE DON'T WANT YOU
GRADUATING WITHOUT HONORS.

01:14:17.453 --> 01:14:20.156
[MOO]

01:14:20.156 --> 01:14:21.424
GOODBYE, GORKY.

01:14:21.424 --> 01:14:23.226
HELLO-O-O...
BESSIE!

01:14:23.226 --> 01:14:25.829
THIS IS EVERETT CALLOWAY
WAKING YOU UP

01:14:25.829 --> 01:14:27.897
ON A BEAUTIFUL
SUNDAY MORNING.

01:14:27.897 --> 01:14:28.698
NEW PAJAMAS?

01:14:28.698 --> 01:14:30.433
YOU LOOK GREAT.

01:14:30.433 --> 01:14:33.603
A REGULAR FASHION PLATE.

01:14:33.603 --> 01:14:36.039
[CHUCKLES]

01:14:36.039 --> 01:14:37.440
OBITUARIES?

01:14:37.440 --> 01:14:40.844
STUDYING UP
TO WRITE MINE.

01:14:40.844 --> 01:14:42.646
I'M COPYING YOU,
HARVARD.

01:14:42.646 --> 01:14:45.214
STUDY FIRST
AND THEN WRITE.

01:14:45.214 --> 01:14:48.317
SOME OF THESE THINGS
ARE REALLY DEPRESSING.

01:14:48.317 --> 01:14:51.254
LOOK AT THIS GUY
BARNEY MILSTEIN,

01:14:51.254 --> 01:14:53.256
THE ONE WITH
THE THREE TACKS.

01:14:53.256 --> 01:14:54.390
"BARNEY MILSTEIN.

01:14:54.390 --> 01:14:55.659
"AGE 79.

01:14:55.659 --> 01:14:56.660
"DIED SATURDAY.

01:14:56.660 --> 01:14:58.261
"NO SURVIVORS.

01:14:58.261 --> 01:14:59.663
NO SERVICES."

01:14:59.663 --> 01:15:02.632
HOW COULD HE DIE?

01:15:02.632 --> 01:15:04.601
HE DIDN'T LIVE.

01:15:07.270 --> 01:15:09.673
I WANT YOU
TO READ MINE,

01:15:09.673 --> 01:15:12.876
JUST WHAT
I GOT SO FAR, ANYWAY.

01:15:12.876 --> 01:15:14.510
LATER.

01:15:16.680 --> 01:15:19.282
I AIN'T FEELING
TOO GOOD, HARVARD.

01:15:19.282 --> 01:15:22.185
I NEED
YOUR OPINION NOW.

01:15:32.295 --> 01:15:33.296
"SIMON WILDER.

01:15:33.296 --> 01:15:35.298
"BORN PORTLAND, MAINE,
1942.

01:15:35.298 --> 01:15:37.701
SON OF HANK AND ANNA."

01:15:37.701 --> 01:15:39.903
[TURNS PAGE]

01:15:39.903 --> 01:15:42.706
"MARRIED 1962
TO LISA THORSTON.

01:15:42.706 --> 01:15:46.042
FATHERED ONE SON
IN 1963."

01:15:47.711 --> 01:15:50.714
"LEFT WIFE AND SON
IN 1963

01:15:50.714 --> 01:15:52.916
TO JOIN
THE MERCHANT MARINE."

01:15:57.721 --> 01:16:01.057
THAT'S AS FAR
AS I GOT.

01:16:02.525 --> 01:16:04.327
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

01:16:07.731 --> 01:16:09.132
I THINK THAT, UH,

01:16:09.132 --> 01:16:11.735
YOU SHOULD PUT THINGS
IN YOUR OBITUARY

01:16:11.735 --> 01:16:14.070
THAT YOU'RE PROUD OF.

01:16:17.741 --> 01:16:20.944
I THOUGHT IT WAS
SUPPOSED TO BE FACTS.

01:16:22.746 --> 01:16:25.348
YOU HAD A WIFE
AND A SON,

01:16:25.348 --> 01:16:27.116
AND YOU LEFT THEM?

01:16:29.152 --> 01:16:31.020
YEAH.

01:16:31.020 --> 01:16:33.289
AND YOU NEVER
CAME BACK?

01:16:33.289 --> 01:16:37.761
IT'S NOT SOMETHING
I'M PROUD OF,
HARVARD.

01:16:38.762 --> 01:16:40.630
THAT'S COMFORTING.

01:16:47.971 --> 01:16:49.372
UH...

01:16:49.372 --> 01:16:51.708
DON'T YOU WANT
TO SEE HIM?

01:16:52.776 --> 01:16:55.812
DO YOU THINK
HE'D FORGIVE ME?

01:17:00.784 --> 01:17:02.451
EAT YOUR BREAKFAST.

01:17:02.451 --> 01:17:07.256
WHAT DID YOUR FATHER
DO TO YOU
THAT WAS SO BAD?

01:17:07.256 --> 01:17:08.658
WHAT DID HE DO?

01:17:08.658 --> 01:17:10.760
HE ABANDONED MY MOTHER.

01:17:10.760 --> 01:17:12.762
I'VE GOT NEWS FOR YOU.

01:17:12.762 --> 01:17:14.764
WHEN IT COMES
TO RELATIONSHIPS,

01:17:14.764 --> 01:17:17.033
EVERYBODY'S
A USED CAR SALESMAN.

01:17:17.033 --> 01:17:18.802
IS THAT YOUR PHILOSOPHY--

01:17:18.802 --> 01:17:20.804
DON'T TRUST ANYONE?

01:17:20.804 --> 01:17:23.807
NO. YOU GOTTA
TRUST PEOPLE.

01:17:23.807 --> 01:17:27.443
YOU JUST CAN'T BELIEVE
IN THE WARRANTY.

01:17:27.443 --> 01:17:29.412
THAT'S CUTE, SIMON.

01:17:29.412 --> 01:17:32.415
THAT'S REALLY
CUTE BULLSHIT.

01:17:32.415 --> 01:17:34.417
HARVARD...

01:17:36.385 --> 01:17:38.221
YOU'D BE SURPRISED

01:17:38.221 --> 01:17:41.424
HOW DIFFERENT
THE VIEW IS
ON THE WAY OUT

01:17:41.424 --> 01:17:44.027
THAN ON THE WAY IN.

01:17:52.836 --> 01:17:55.438
[BUGS BUNNY]
EH, WHAT'S UP, DOC?

01:17:55.438 --> 01:17:56.840
HERE I AM.

01:17:56.840 --> 01:17:58.441
OH, HELLO,
HELLO, HELLO.

01:17:58.441 --> 01:17:59.843
CAN I SHUT THIS OFF?

01:17:59.843 --> 01:18:01.444
JUST
A COTTON-PICKIN'--

01:18:01.444 --> 01:18:02.846
I HAVE TWO INVITES

01:18:02.846 --> 01:18:04.247
TO THE LYNX.

01:18:04.247 --> 01:18:06.850
THIS CARD WILL ADMIT
YOU AND A GUEST

01:18:06.850 --> 01:18:09.853
TO THE GREATEST BASH
OF THE YEAR.

01:18:09.853 --> 01:18:12.255
FOR YOU AND THE FACE,
I PRESUME.

01:18:12.255 --> 01:18:15.258
UGH! THAT MEANS
I'LL HAVE TO MAKE UP
WITH HIM AGAIN.

01:18:15.258 --> 01:18:17.460
MONTY! WHERE IS HE?
IS HE UPSTAIRS?

01:18:17.460 --> 01:18:19.462
TO THE LYNX?
GREAT! I'M READY.

01:18:19.462 --> 01:18:20.864
I'M SORRY, JEFF.

01:18:20.864 --> 01:18:23.632
I COULDN'T WORM
ANOTHER ONE OUT OF THEM.

01:18:23.632 --> 01:18:24.633
HELLO.

01:18:24.633 --> 01:18:26.736
FOR YOU,
LORD MONTAGUE.

01:18:26.736 --> 01:18:27.871
GREAT.

01:18:27.871 --> 01:18:29.873
THAT'S O.K.
MONTY'S A MONK.

01:18:29.873 --> 01:18:31.875
HE'LL TAKE ME
AS HIS DATE.

01:18:31.875 --> 01:18:34.778
SORRY, JEFF.
I'VE ALREADY
GOT A DATE.

01:18:36.079 --> 01:18:37.080
YOU DO?

01:18:37.080 --> 01:18:38.481
YEAH.

01:18:38.481 --> 01:18:40.817
I'M TAKING SIMON.

01:18:48.291 --> 01:18:50.626
SO, I GUESS I'LL
TAKE YOU, JEFF.

01:18:50.626 --> 01:18:51.861
GREAT.

01:18:51.861 --> 01:18:54.630
WHAT ABOUT THE FACE?

01:18:54.630 --> 01:18:56.299
HE CAN FEND
FOR HIMSELF.

01:18:56.299 --> 01:18:59.502
SO WHAT ARE YOU WEARING
ON YOUR DATE?

01:18:59.502 --> 01:19:00.904
OH, I DON'T KNOW

01:19:00.904 --> 01:19:02.305
BECAUSE MY EVENING GOWN

01:19:02.305 --> 01:19:04.507
HASN'T COME BACK
FROM THE CLEANERS.

01:19:04.507 --> 01:19:06.509
HONEY, HASN'T
ANYONE TOLD YOU?

01:19:06.509 --> 01:19:09.512
LYNX IS
A PAJAMA PARTY.

01:19:09.512 --> 01:19:12.248
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:19:17.753 --> 01:19:19.055
BOY, OH, BOY,
OH, BOY.

01:19:19.055 --> 01:19:20.656
DID ANYBODY
EVER TELL YOU

01:19:20.656 --> 01:19:22.258
YOU LOOK JUST LIKE
MARILYN?

01:19:22.258 --> 01:19:23.259
MONROE?

01:19:23.259 --> 01:19:24.060
NO, SCHWARTZ.

01:19:24.060 --> 01:19:26.062
HER FATHER
OWNS A DELI

01:19:26.062 --> 01:19:28.464
WHERE WE GET
THIS KNOCKWURST
THAT'S THE BEST.

01:19:28.464 --> 01:19:31.067
THERE'S A BOY
THAT KNOWS HOW
TO WEAR SILK.

01:19:31.067 --> 01:19:33.669
HE'S COVERING
A TRAGIC BIRTHMARK.

01:19:33.669 --> 01:19:35.071
AREN'T YOU
WHITMAN'S GHOST?

01:19:35.071 --> 01:19:38.074
YOU'LL HARDLY KNOW
WHO I AM OR WHAT I MEAN.

01:19:38.074 --> 01:19:39.675
YOU SHOULDN'T BE WITH ME.

01:19:39.675 --> 01:19:41.077
AM I CRAMPING
YOUR STYLE?

01:19:41.077 --> 01:19:43.079
LOOK AT HER.
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

01:19:43.079 --> 01:19:44.680
YOU HAVE GOOD TASTE.

01:19:44.680 --> 01:19:48.017
AND YOU'RE
IN LOVE WITH HER.

01:19:50.719 --> 01:19:51.821
SO WHAT?

01:19:51.821 --> 01:19:52.822
SO WHAT?

01:19:52.822 --> 01:19:54.423
YEAH. SO WHAT?

01:19:54.423 --> 01:19:55.424
SO WHAT?

01:19:55.424 --> 01:19:56.425
THAT'S EVERYTHING.

01:19:56.425 --> 01:19:57.827
NOT TO HER
IT ISN'T.

01:19:57.827 --> 01:20:00.096
SO PROVE HER WRONG.

01:20:00.096 --> 01:20:03.099
I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO GET HER TO ADMIT

01:20:03.099 --> 01:20:04.700
SHE'S WRONG
ABOUT ANYTHING.

01:20:04.700 --> 01:20:06.069
THAT PROVES
SHE LOVES YOU.

01:20:06.069 --> 01:20:08.604
WHAT ARE YOU
WAITING FOR?

01:20:08.604 --> 01:20:11.640
"TO DRIVE FREE,
TO LOVE FREE,

01:20:11.640 --> 01:20:13.642
"TO COURT DESTRUCTION
WITH TAUNTS,

01:20:13.642 --> 01:20:16.045
"TO FEED
THE REMAINDER OF LIFE

01:20:16.045 --> 01:20:18.982
"WITH ONE HOUR
OF FULLNESS AND FREEDOM,

01:20:18.982 --> 01:20:21.117
"ONE BRIEF HOUR

01:20:21.117 --> 01:20:23.719
OF MADNESS AND JOY."

01:20:23.719 --> 01:20:26.755
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO DANCE?

01:20:26.755 --> 01:20:28.391
UH, MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T.

01:20:28.391 --> 01:20:31.995
LET'S NOT GO OVERBOARD
WITH THIS STAYIN' ALIVE
JUNK.

01:20:31.995 --> 01:20:33.897
YES, I WOULD.
JUST A MINUTE.

01:20:33.897 --> 01:20:35.831
DON'T LET HER
BE A REGRET.

01:20:35.831 --> 01:20:37.967
IT'S WORSE THAN
BEING A LOSER.

01:20:38.935 --> 01:20:40.536
WHAT'S YOUR NAME,
HONEY?

01:20:40.536 --> 01:20:41.537
MARTY.

01:20:41.537 --> 01:20:42.571
WHAT'S YOUR MAJOR, MARTY?

01:20:42.571 --> 01:20:43.572
FRENCH.

01:20:43.572 --> 01:20:44.974
[COURTNEY]
LEAVE ME ALONE!

01:20:44.974 --> 01:20:46.375
JUST
FORGET ABOUT IT!

01:20:46.375 --> 01:20:47.776
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

01:20:47.776 --> 01:20:50.313
HEY, BABY.
DON'T BE THAT WAY!

01:20:50.313 --> 01:20:52.748
YOU'RE ALWAYS
TELLING ME HOW TO ACT!

01:20:52.748 --> 01:20:55.751
I'M TIRED OF YOU
TELLING ME WHAT TO DO!

01:20:55.751 --> 01:20:58.154
SUCH A JERK.

01:20:58.154 --> 01:21:01.290
* I REACH IN SLOWLY *

01:21:01.290 --> 01:21:05.094
* JUST LIKE I WAS BLIND *

01:21:07.230 --> 01:21:10.666
* I HEAR VOICES *

01:21:10.666 --> 01:21:14.370
* THAT I DON'T
RECOGNIZE... **

01:21:26.182 --> 01:21:27.783
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:21:27.783 --> 01:21:29.552
I'M ENDING OUR FRIENDSHIP.

01:21:50.406 --> 01:21:52.075
[THUMP]

01:21:53.776 --> 01:21:54.777
COURTNEY.

01:21:54.777 --> 01:21:55.778
HMM?

01:21:55.778 --> 01:21:57.080
WAKE UP.

01:21:58.847 --> 01:22:00.816
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

01:22:00.816 --> 01:22:02.818
WHAT'S WRONG?

01:22:02.818 --> 01:22:04.420
WHAT'S WRONG?

01:22:04.420 --> 01:22:05.421
SIMON.

01:22:05.421 --> 01:22:06.822
[COUGHING]

01:22:06.822 --> 01:22:09.825
DO YOU THINK
THERE'S A HELL?

01:22:09.825 --> 01:22:12.428
WE'VE GOT TO GET HIM
TO A HOSPITAL.

01:22:12.428 --> 01:22:13.429
NO.

01:22:13.429 --> 01:22:15.831
I PROMISED HIM.

01:22:15.831 --> 01:22:19.035
I DIDN'T WANT
TO BE ALONE.

01:22:20.869 --> 01:22:22.238
[THUNDER]

01:22:22.238 --> 01:22:24.840
I'LL GO GET YOU
SOME WATER, O.K.?

01:22:24.840 --> 01:22:26.042
THANKS.

01:22:28.844 --> 01:22:31.447
HEY, COULD YOU, UH,

01:22:31.447 --> 01:22:33.249
WOULD YOU...

01:22:33.249 --> 01:22:36.552
JUST SIT HERE
FOR A WHILE?

01:22:40.856 --> 01:22:42.858
HEY...

01:22:42.858 --> 01:22:43.859
COME ON.

01:22:43.859 --> 01:22:45.461
YOU ALWAYS BOUNCE BACK.

01:22:45.461 --> 01:22:46.862
YEAH.

01:22:46.862 --> 01:22:48.864
WHEN I WAS KID,
I HAD A DOG,

01:22:48.864 --> 01:22:50.266
A FUNNY-LOOKING
THING--

01:22:50.266 --> 01:22:53.469
ORANGE HAIR,
BIG EARS...

01:22:53.469 --> 01:22:55.871
SKINNY BODY.

01:22:55.871 --> 01:22:58.874
HE USED TO LOVE
TO CHASE CARS.

01:22:58.874 --> 01:23:01.544
HE GOT RUN OVER
THREE TIMES.

01:23:03.279 --> 01:23:05.281
HE NEVER REALLY
GOT HURT.

01:23:05.281 --> 01:23:07.283
HE'D GO HIDE
UNDER THE COUCH

01:23:07.283 --> 01:23:08.884
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS.

01:23:08.884 --> 01:23:10.219
WHEN HE CAME OUT,

01:23:10.219 --> 01:23:13.222
HE'D GO RIGHT BACK
TO CHASING CARS AGAIN.

01:23:13.222 --> 01:23:15.891
EVENTUALLY,
HE GOT OLD AND SICK.

01:23:15.891 --> 01:23:18.894
GOD, WAS HE UGLY.

01:23:18.894 --> 01:23:21.297
TOWARDS THE END,

01:23:21.297 --> 01:23:24.900
HE WENT OFF IN THE WOODS
TO DIE ALONE.

01:23:24.900 --> 01:23:27.903
HE LAID ON
A PILE OF LEAVES

01:23:27.903 --> 01:23:29.905
PERFECTLY STILL.

01:23:29.905 --> 01:23:31.907
YOU COULDN'T MOVE HIM.

01:23:31.907 --> 01:23:33.909
IF YOU TRIED
TO TOUCH HIM,

01:23:33.909 --> 01:23:35.778
HE'D SNAP AT YOU.

01:23:35.778 --> 01:23:38.647
HERE YOU GO.

01:23:38.647 --> 01:23:40.516
THANKS.

01:23:44.920 --> 01:23:46.455
I'M SCARED.

01:23:46.455 --> 01:23:48.457
HEY, I'M HERE.

01:23:50.193 --> 01:23:52.595
MONTY, IF I GET
THROUGH TONIGHT,

01:23:52.595 --> 01:23:56.031
WOULD YOU DRIVE ME
SOMEPLACE TOMORROW?

01:23:57.800 --> 01:23:59.402
YEAH. SURE.

01:23:59.402 --> 01:24:00.803
TOMORROW?

01:24:02.171 --> 01:24:03.206
YEAH, TOMORROW.

01:24:03.206 --> 01:24:06.275
TOMORROW'S FINE.

01:24:07.710 --> 01:24:09.778
I WANT
TO SEE MY SON...

01:24:11.080 --> 01:24:13.416
JUST ONCE.

01:24:28.231 --> 01:24:31.234
WHAT ABOUT HIS THESIS?
DID HE HAND IT IN?

01:24:31.234 --> 01:24:32.835
I DON'T KNOW.

01:24:32.835 --> 01:24:34.837
IT'S DUE TODAY.
HE KNOWS.

01:24:36.839 --> 01:24:38.841
EVERETT,
LET'S GO!

01:24:40.843 --> 01:24:42.245
FINISHED MY THESIS.

01:24:42.245 --> 01:24:44.847
IT'S NOT SO GREAT,
BUT IT'S DONE.

01:24:44.847 --> 01:24:45.848
CONGRATULATIONS.
EVERETT!

01:24:45.848 --> 01:24:46.849
YES!

01:24:46.849 --> 01:24:49.252
SO...
WHAT ABOUT YOURS?

01:24:49.252 --> 01:24:51.254
DID YOU
HAND IT IN ALREADY?

01:24:51.254 --> 01:24:54.257
NOT DONE.
I'VE GOT TO TYPE UP
A BIBLIOGRAPHY.

01:24:54.257 --> 01:24:57.260
YOU'LL BE ON THE ROAD.
HOW WILL YOU FINISH IT?

01:24:57.260 --> 01:24:58.394
I GUESS I WON'T.

01:24:58.394 --> 01:25:00.496
DID PITKANNAN
GIVE YOU AN EXTENSION?

01:25:00.496 --> 01:25:01.797
NO.

01:25:09.872 --> 01:25:12.007
MONTY...

01:25:12.007 --> 01:25:13.642
CAN I COME?

01:25:15.178 --> 01:25:16.812
YEAH.

01:25:23.051 --> 01:25:27.190
* I MUST BE GOIN' *

01:25:27.190 --> 01:25:31.660
* KISS ME GOODBYE *

01:25:31.660 --> 01:25:34.830
* ALL THE COLORS
ARE CHANGIN' *

01:25:34.830 --> 01:25:36.365
TURN IT AROUND.

01:25:36.365 --> 01:25:39.835
* THERE'S A TEAR
IN MY EYE *

01:25:39.835 --> 01:25:41.370
NO, THE OTHER WAY.

01:25:41.370 --> 01:25:45.208
* AND I'M GOIN' FREE *

01:25:45.208 --> 01:25:49.978
* FOR THE REST
OF MY LIFE *

01:25:49.978 --> 01:25:54.850
* AND I NEVER GO RUNNIN' *

01:25:54.850 --> 01:25:59.855
* ON THE WRONG SIDE *

01:25:59.855 --> 01:26:04.227
* OH-OH *

01:26:04.227 --> 01:26:07.363
* OH-OH-OH-OH *

01:26:07.363 --> 01:26:12.100
* I NEVER GO RUNNIN' *

01:26:12.100 --> 01:26:17.540
* ON THE WRONG SIDE **

01:26:30.286 --> 01:26:31.687
HELLO,
UH, MR. WILDER.

01:26:31.687 --> 01:26:33.889
UH, MY NAME'S
MONTY KESSLER.

01:26:33.889 --> 01:26:35.791
I'M A STUDENT
AT HARVARD.

01:26:35.791 --> 01:26:38.294
I GUESS IT WAS ABOUT
THREE MONTHS AGO

01:26:38.294 --> 01:26:39.895
I MET YOUR FATHER,

01:26:39.895 --> 01:26:41.297
AND HE'S IN THAT VAN.

01:26:41.297 --> 01:26:43.198
HE WANTS TO SEE YOU.

01:26:46.902 --> 01:26:48.304
I DON'T HAVE A FATHER.

01:26:48.304 --> 01:26:50.306
PLEASE. HE'S VERY ILL.

01:26:50.306 --> 01:26:53.108
HE JUST WANTS TO SEE YOU
FOR A FEW MINUTES.

01:26:53.108 --> 01:26:54.977
I DON'T WANT
TO SEE HIM.

01:26:54.977 --> 01:26:57.346
HE'S DYING.

01:26:58.714 --> 01:27:01.717
PLEASE, JUST WALK OVER
FOR A COUPLE OF MINUTES,

01:27:01.717 --> 01:27:04.320
SAY HELLO,
LET HIM LOOK AT YOU,

01:27:04.320 --> 01:27:05.721
AND THEN WE'LL GO,

01:27:05.721 --> 01:27:08.924
AND YOU NEVER
HAVE TO SEE HIM AGAIN.

01:27:12.928 --> 01:27:14.530
O.K.

01:27:35.351 --> 01:27:38.554
IS THERE SOMETHING
YOU WANT FROM ME?

01:27:40.723 --> 01:27:44.827
I JUST WANTED
TO LOOK AT YOU.

01:27:44.827 --> 01:27:46.862
FINE.

01:27:46.862 --> 01:27:48.697
HAVE A LOOK.

